WEBVTT

1
00:00:07,166 --> 00:00:09,375
(CHORAL INTRO MUSIC PLAYING)

2
00:00:15,875 --> 00:00:17,208
(ROARS)

3
00:00:21,958 --> 00:00:24,583
(HEROIC SYNTH-ROCK
MUSIC PLAYING)

4
00:00:50,166 --> 00:00:51,500
MAN: <i>Where do I start?</i>

5
00:00:51,666 --> 00:00:55,166
<i>Well, I guess what I really</i>
<i>want to say is,</i>

6
00:00:55,333 --> 00:00:59,416
<i>everything I am is because of</i>
<i>where I come from.</i>

7
00:00:59,541 --> 00:01:01,791
(MUSIC CONTINUES)

8
00:01:01,916 --> 00:01:06,166
<i>Eternia,</i>
<i>a world of endless beauty.</i>

9
00:01:07,166 --> 00:01:09,000
<i>All that stuff</i>
<i>that only exists</i>

10
00:01:09,125 --> 00:01:11,500
<i>in legends</i>
<i>and bedtime stories.</i>

11
00:01:11,666 --> 00:01:15,208
<i>On Eternia,</i>
<i>that stuff is real.</i>

12
00:01:16,416 --> 00:01:19,625
<i>Griffins, dragons,</i>
<i>talking tigers,</i>

13
00:01:20,208 --> 00:01:22,791
<i>enchanted forests,</i>
<i>burning deserts,</i>

14
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:25,041
<i>islands in the sky.</i>
<i>You name it.</i>

15
00:01:25,750 --> 00:01:28,166
<i>I... I swear I'm not high.</i>

16
00:01:28,291 --> 00:01:29,291
(ENGINE WHOOSHES)

17
00:01:30,083 --> 00:01:34,000
<i>And then</i>
<i>we've got Castle Grayskull.</i>

18
00:01:34,708 --> 00:01:36,083
<i>My father once told me</i>

19
00:01:36,208 --> 00:01:39,666
<i>that Eternia is the beating</i>
<i>heart of the cosmos.</i>

20
00:01:40,125 --> 00:01:43,333
<i>And Grayskull</i>
<i>is the heart of that heart.</i>

21
00:01:43,666 --> 00:01:47,583
<i>So, I... I guess the, uh...</i>
<i>the heart of the heart</i>

22
00:01:47,750 --> 00:01:52,125
<i>of, uh, the heart</i>
<i>is the Power of Grayskull.</i>

23
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:56,916
<i>They say it can make a man</i>
<i>as mighty as a god.</i>

24
00:01:58,166 --> 00:02:02,000
<i>To keep it safe, the Power</i>
<i>was bound within a vessel.</i>

25
00:02:02,416 --> 00:02:07,416
<i>An ancient sword they called</i>
<i>the Sword of Power.</i>

26
00:02:08,083 --> 00:02:10,041
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)
<i>Yeah, I know,</i>

27
00:02:10,166 --> 00:02:11,583
<i>but that's what</i>
<i>they went with.</i>

28
00:02:12,791 --> 00:02:16,541
<i>Legend said that when Eternia</i>
<i>was in its greatest need,</i>

29
00:02:16,708 --> 00:02:19,833
<i>a hero would step forth</i>
<i>and wield the Sword,</i>

30
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:23,916
<i>and, you know, use it...</i>

31
00:02:24,708 --> 00:02:26,083
<i>awesomely.</i>

32
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:29,458
<i>Until that day, it was locked</i>
<i>away within the castle</i>

33
00:02:29,625 --> 00:02:32,541
<i>under the watchful eye</i>
<i>of the Sorceress,</i>

34
00:02:32,708 --> 00:02:35,541
<i>who was wise, and ancient,</i>

35
00:02:35,708 --> 00:02:37,625
<i>and a little scary,</i>
<i>to be honest.</i>

36
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:40,500
<i>But she's cool.</i>
<i>She's... She's cool.</i>

37
00:02:41,666 --> 00:02:44,166
<i>For hundreds of years,</i>
<i>Grayskull has remained</i>

38
00:02:44,291 --> 00:02:46,666
<i>under the protection</i>
<i>of my ancestors.</i>

39
00:02:47,125 --> 00:02:48,666
<i>See, I come from</i>

40
00:02:48,791 --> 00:02:51,708
<i>a pretty impressive lineage</i>
<i>of mighty heroes.</i>

41
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:56,791
<i>Noble, strong, fearless.</i>

42
00:02:56,958 --> 00:03:00,041
But, Mom,
I don't want to fight.

43
00:03:00,583 --> 00:03:03,000
Everyone's bigger than me
and stronger.

44
00:03:03,166 --> 00:03:05,083
And I have poor
hand-eye coordination.

45
00:03:05,250 --> 00:03:07,833
-Nonsense! Who told you that?
-BOY: Cringer.

46
00:03:08,208 --> 00:03:11,000
It's true. He's the smallest
and the weakest.

47
00:03:11,166 --> 00:03:14,416
It's a miracle he hasn't
broken any bones or died.

48
00:03:15,333 --> 00:03:17,125
So, what should
the prince be doing

49
00:03:17,250 --> 00:03:19,083
instead of arms training, hmm?

50
00:03:19,250 --> 00:03:22,250
I don't know, maybe hanging
out and playing with Cringer.

51
00:03:22,416 --> 00:03:25,125
You go. I'll find a ball
of yarn and I'm good.

52
00:03:25,291 --> 00:03:26,708
You're zero help, you know.

53
00:03:27,458 --> 00:03:29,000
Do I have to go?

54
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:32,958
-Arms training. Now.
-(SIGHS)

55
00:03:41,083 --> 00:03:45,416
Listen up,
future finest of Eternos.

56
00:03:46,166 --> 00:03:49,833
There are no statues
of losers,

57
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:53,083
no streets
named after cowards,

58
00:03:53,250 --> 00:03:57,666
and there are no parades
for doing your best.

59
00:03:57,833 --> 00:04:01,916
This ground, that palace,
your entire lives

60
00:04:02,083 --> 00:04:03,750
are built on the backs
of men and women

61
00:04:03,875 --> 00:04:06,833
who have won the fight.

62
00:04:07,416 --> 00:04:09,458
And as your
king's Man-At-Arms,

63
00:04:09,583 --> 00:04:12,375
you can bet
I won a lot of fights.

64
00:04:12,541 --> 00:04:14,875
That's why we're all here.

65
00:04:15,041 --> 00:04:18,416
I saved your mom
and dad's asses.

66
00:04:18,583 --> 00:04:20,250
I saved your neighbor's asses.

67
00:04:20,375 --> 00:04:22,583
I saved your neighbor's
mom and dad's asses.

68
00:04:22,750 --> 00:04:24,166
That is a lot of asses.

69
00:04:24,291 --> 00:04:26,916
You know what, the point is
I fought for you,

70
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:30,833
and now you are going to fight
for me with keen reflexes,

71
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:35,500
sure aim, and glorious muscle.

72
00:04:36,375 --> 00:04:37,583
And this.

73
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:39,500
Anybody know what it is?

74
00:04:39,875 --> 00:04:41,000
It's a stick.

75
00:04:43,833 --> 00:04:44,916
(MAN-AT-ARMS GRUNTS)

76
00:04:45,708 --> 00:04:47,958
Thank you
for stating the obvious.

77
00:04:49,291 --> 00:04:50,291
Anybody else?

78
00:04:50,958 --> 00:04:51,958
Teela?

79
00:04:52,541 --> 00:04:53,666
Your arms.

80
00:04:53,875 --> 00:04:55,041
That's my girl!

81
00:04:56,625 --> 00:05:01,625
These are your arms.
They are an extension of you.

82
00:05:01,791 --> 00:05:03,833
All right, partner up. Arm up.

83
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,750
I want to see big,
shiny bruises.

84
00:05:06,916 --> 00:05:11,083
I want to see bloody noses.
I want to see chipped teeth.

85
00:05:11,250 --> 00:05:13,208
Okay, let's go.
Anchor your weight.

86
00:05:13,333 --> 00:05:14,541
PRINCE: Hey, Dian.
Do you want to... (GROANS)

87
00:05:14,666 --> 00:05:16,208
MAN-AT-ARMS: If this was real,
you just died twice.

88
00:05:16,333 --> 00:05:17,875
(TRAINEES LAUGH)

89
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:19,875
-Adam.
-MAN-AT-ARMS: Eyes up!

90
00:05:20,041 --> 00:05:21,583
You got to look him in the eye
when you smash him

91
00:05:21,708 --> 00:05:23,041
-in the face.
-(GROANS)

92
00:05:23,416 --> 00:05:25,416
Parry or next time
it'll be harder.

93
00:05:25,791 --> 00:05:27,333
Maybe we could just sit down
and talk about this?

94
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:32,083
Hey, Adam. Adam.
Just do what you can, okay?

95
00:05:32,708 --> 00:05:35,041
Yeah. Teela.

96
00:05:36,041 --> 00:05:37,416
-(TEELA GRUNTS)
-Aah!

97
00:05:38,416 --> 00:05:39,708
What kind of a friend are you?

98
00:05:39,875 --> 00:05:41,333
The kind
that's going to beat you.

99
00:05:42,333 --> 00:05:44,166
(GIGGLING)

100
00:05:45,083 --> 00:05:47,291
(MAJESTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

101
00:05:54,541 --> 00:05:55,541
Duncan.

102
00:05:56,416 --> 00:05:58,666
(TRAINEES GIGGLING)

103
00:05:58,791 --> 00:06:01,541
How do you think
our novices are faring?

104
00:06:02,708 --> 00:06:05,250
They're a fine
and diligent bunch, Sire.

105
00:06:06,041 --> 00:06:07,041
All of them?

106
00:06:07,208 --> 00:06:08,750
TEELA: No dancing, Adam.
(CHUCKLES)

107
00:06:09,375 --> 00:06:10,375
DUNCAN: Mm-hmm.

108
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:12,750
-TEELA: Come on.
-Hit me! Hit me!

109
00:06:12,958 --> 00:06:14,708
He's making
a fool out of himself.

110
00:06:14,875 --> 00:06:17,791
I promised to make him
into a man, and I will.

111
00:06:17,958 --> 00:06:20,625
Yeah. But what kind of man?

112
00:06:20,791 --> 00:06:23,083
-TEELA: Adam! (GIGGLING)
-Just hit me!

113
00:06:23,541 --> 00:06:24,708
-(ADAM GRUNTS)
-(LAUGHS)

114
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:27,500
Well, he did disarm her.

115
00:06:27,791 --> 00:06:30,250
That's not
how this works, old friend.

116
00:06:30,958 --> 00:06:32,625
ADAM: I win! I win! I win!

117
00:06:33,708 --> 00:06:35,666
TEELA: You're being silly,
Adam.

118
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,000
Boy.

119
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:45,000
Face me. With this.

120
00:06:48,458 --> 00:06:49,458
Well, pick it up.

121
00:06:52,708 --> 00:06:54,041
(SWORD RINGS)

122
00:06:55,916 --> 00:06:56,916
Now...

123
00:06:59,791 --> 00:07:01,333
defend yourself.

124
00:07:01,458 --> 00:07:02,458
(GASPING)

125
00:07:02,583 --> 00:07:04,500
-(GRUNTING)
-Dad.

126
00:07:04,791 --> 00:07:05,791
Dad!

127
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:10,041
(GROANS, PANTS)

128
00:07:11,416 --> 00:07:14,125
This world
is no place for the weak.

129
00:07:14,541 --> 00:07:15,833
Yes, Dad.

130
00:07:16,666 --> 00:07:17,666
Now say it.

131
00:07:19,875 --> 00:07:23,416
This world
is no place for the weak.

132
00:07:24,250 --> 00:07:25,291
Hmm.

133
00:07:29,583 --> 00:07:30,666
(SWORD RINGS)

134
00:07:32,625 --> 00:07:34,458
Adam. Get up!

135
00:07:35,291 --> 00:07:36,291
Get up.

136
00:07:36,875 --> 00:07:38,041
When you fall,

137
00:07:39,416 --> 00:07:43,791
this is your chance
to stand tall. Okay?

138
00:07:45,041 --> 00:07:46,333
Now look strong.

139
00:07:46,500 --> 00:07:49,750
When he turns around,
he's going to see you.

140
00:07:49,916 --> 00:07:52,750
And you want to show him
you can take a hit.

141
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:55,333
When he turns around,

142
00:07:55,458 --> 00:07:57,583
he's not going to see
a frightened little boy.

143
00:07:57,708 --> 00:07:59,250
He's going to see a man.

144
00:07:59,416 --> 00:08:00,625
What's he going to see?

145
00:08:01,083 --> 00:08:03,291
-A man.
-DUNCAN: Good. Look.

146
00:08:03,625 --> 00:08:05,166
As soon as he turns around.

147
00:08:09,916 --> 00:08:11,041
(SIGHS)

148
00:08:15,666 --> 00:08:16,791
Walk it off, lad.

149
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:20,750
(MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING)

150
00:08:24,166 --> 00:08:27,250
Show's over.
Back to work. Let's go.

151
00:08:28,541 --> 00:08:30,750
(PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING)

152
00:08:39,500 --> 00:08:41,375
-Adam.
-(GASPS)

153
00:08:41,500 --> 00:08:42,500
What are you doing here?

154
00:08:42,666 --> 00:08:44,208
Following you.

155
00:08:44,583 --> 00:08:48,125
Yeah, well,
I came here to be alone, so...

156
00:08:48,291 --> 00:08:49,458
Don't be such a squink.

157
00:08:50,375 --> 00:08:51,375
(SIGHS)

158
00:08:52,583 --> 00:08:54,750
I didn't think
you were weak, you know.

159
00:08:55,208 --> 00:08:57,208
Today at training.

160
00:08:58,125 --> 00:08:59,583
My dad did.

161
00:09:06,583 --> 00:09:10,083
Is that... the Sorceress?

162
00:09:12,500 --> 00:09:13,625
ADAM: What is she looking at?

163
00:09:13,750 --> 00:09:14,750
(OBJECT WHIZZING)

164
00:09:14,875 --> 00:09:16,500
-(EXPLOSION)
-(BOTH GASP)

165
00:09:17,916 --> 00:09:19,916
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

166
00:09:32,291 --> 00:09:34,250
DUNCAN: King Randor,
we are under attack.

167
00:09:36,583 --> 00:09:39,041
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

168
00:09:40,708 --> 00:09:42,416
I have this in hand, Sire.

169
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:45,166
The Royal Guard
are trained for this.

170
00:09:45,291 --> 00:09:46,958
(GUARDS YELP)

171
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:48,500
(GASPS)

172
00:09:49,125 --> 00:09:51,458
(ALL YELLING AND SNARLING)

173
00:09:54,916 --> 00:09:56,916
(ROARS)

174
00:09:58,041 --> 00:10:00,083
(ALL GRUNTING)

175
00:10:00,833 --> 00:10:02,000
(ALL YELL)

176
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:08,500
(GRUNTS)

177
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:12,000
(ALL GROAN)

178
00:10:13,791 --> 00:10:15,125
(WARRIORS GROANING)

179
00:10:15,708 --> 00:10:17,541
(GRUNTS, WHIMPERS)

180
00:10:20,541 --> 00:10:21,833
(ELECTRICAL BEEPS)

181
00:10:23,666 --> 00:10:24,791
(SCREAMING)

182
00:10:28,375 --> 00:10:30,833
(SCREAMS)

183
00:10:30,958 --> 00:10:32,000
(SCREAMS)

184
00:10:32,875 --> 00:10:34,750
(ALL GRUNTING)

185
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,166
(BOTH GASP)

186
00:10:39,291 --> 00:10:40,500
-(SIGHS)
-(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

187
00:10:41,708 --> 00:10:43,166
I promise,

188
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:46,666
no harm will come to you
nor your family.

189
00:10:46,833 --> 00:10:49,500
I'll get you safely
to Grayskull. Guards!

190
00:10:50,875 --> 00:10:51,875
KING RANDOR: Hey, it's okay.

191
00:10:52,541 --> 00:10:53,541
Stay close.

192
00:10:55,541 --> 00:10:56,625
DUNCAN: Teela! Come on.

193
00:10:56,791 --> 00:10:57,791
Dad...

194
00:10:58,416 --> 00:10:59,416
I'm scared.

195
00:10:59,833 --> 00:11:03,166
Who taught you that word?
Huh? Not me.

196
00:11:03,333 --> 00:11:05,125
It's going
to be all right, pet.

197
00:11:05,541 --> 00:11:08,000
Whatever happens,
as long as I'm here,

198
00:11:08,125 --> 00:11:10,416
you have nothing to fear.
All right?

199
00:11:11,666 --> 00:11:12,750
Come on. Come on.

200
00:11:12,875 --> 00:11:14,875
(PANICKED SHOUTING)

201
00:11:20,958 --> 00:11:22,833
(WARRIORS GROANING)

202
00:11:22,958 --> 00:11:25,208
Now go! Go, go!

203
00:11:27,750 --> 00:11:28,750
There's too many of them.

204
00:11:28,875 --> 00:11:30,250
A big army
only means one thing.

205
00:11:32,916 --> 00:11:34,250
More targets.

206
00:11:35,333 --> 00:11:37,250
(STIRRING ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

207
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:39,416
(GROANING AND GRUNTING)

208
00:11:46,833 --> 00:11:47,833
(SHOUTS)

209
00:11:49,916 --> 00:11:51,458
(PANTING)

210
00:11:53,250 --> 00:11:54,375
Go, go!

211
00:11:59,208 --> 00:12:00,375
DUNCAN: Follow me.

212
00:12:01,541 --> 00:12:02,666
We're going this way.

213
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:10,083
All right, just stay there.

214
00:12:12,958 --> 00:12:14,500
(DUNCAN GRUNTS)

215
00:12:14,625 --> 00:12:16,166
(SCREAMS)

216
00:12:16,291 --> 00:12:18,291
(GRUNTING)

217
00:12:28,541 --> 00:12:30,541
(PANTING)

218
00:12:31,166 --> 00:12:33,750
(HEAVY FOOTSTEPS)

219
00:12:39,208 --> 00:12:41,583
(EVIL LAUGHTER)

220
00:12:43,083 --> 00:12:46,083
Weak little palace boys.

221
00:12:46,916 --> 00:12:49,500
Sire, go and don't stop.

222
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:52,375
Go. I'll settle this.

223
00:12:54,416 --> 00:12:56,083
Somebody wants to brawl.

224
00:13:01,458 --> 00:13:03,000
(CHUCKLES)

225
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:06,583
(GRUNTING RHYTHMICALLY)

226
00:13:06,708 --> 00:13:08,166
That's far enough.

227
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:13,000
(DRAMATIC ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

228
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:18,041
(YELLS)

229
00:13:18,166 --> 00:13:19,916
(GRUNTING)

230
00:13:29,583 --> 00:13:31,458
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

231
00:13:33,166 --> 00:13:35,166
-(GRUNTING)
-(GROANING)

232
00:14:00,541 --> 00:14:02,791
(BOTH STRAINING)

233
00:14:04,208 --> 00:14:05,750
-(DUNCAN GRUNTS)
-(GROANS)

234
00:14:06,166 --> 00:14:08,166
-(GRUNTING)
-(GROANING)

235
00:14:13,666 --> 00:14:15,000
(COUGHS)

236
00:14:17,250 --> 00:14:19,666
How dare
you come into my city!

237
00:14:19,791 --> 00:14:21,083
Don't you know
who you're messing with?

238
00:14:21,583 --> 00:14:23,083
Why don't you tell me.

239
00:14:23,250 --> 00:14:27,375
I am Duncan,
Commander of the Royal Guard.

240
00:14:27,916 --> 00:14:29,833
(GRUNTING)

241
00:14:29,958 --> 00:14:32,000
-(PANTS)
-(GRUNTS)

242
00:14:32,125 --> 00:14:34,791
The King's goddamn
Man-At-Arms.

243
00:14:34,916 --> 00:14:36,208
-(GRUNTS)
-(GROANS)

244
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:37,750
And today...

245
00:14:37,875 --> 00:14:39,916
-(METAL SQUEAKS)
-WARRIOR: And today...

246
00:14:40,041 --> 00:14:42,000
-(WHIRRING AND CLICKING)
-(GROWLS)

247
00:14:43,125 --> 00:14:44,416
-(DUNCAN GASPS)
-(GRUNTS)

248
00:14:46,125 --> 00:14:47,333
You failed.

249
00:14:47,458 --> 00:14:48,875
-(BEEPS, FIRES)
-(DUNCAN GRUNTS)

250
00:14:52,250 --> 00:14:53,291
(SHUDDERS)

251
00:14:53,750 --> 00:14:54,875
(CHUCKLES)

252
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,875
(BEEPING)

253
00:15:05,916 --> 00:15:08,416
Dad. Dad.

254
00:15:08,583 --> 00:15:12,333
Okay, come on. On your feet.
Get up. Come on. Please.

255
00:15:12,541 --> 00:15:13,583
Teela.

256
00:15:14,166 --> 00:15:15,916
-I failed.
-(BEEPING FASTER)

257
00:15:16,041 --> 00:15:17,041
(GROANS)

258
00:15:21,375 --> 00:15:22,375
TEELA: Come on.

259
00:15:22,500 --> 00:15:23,625
(BEEPING RAPIDLY)

260
00:15:23,958 --> 00:15:25,625
Hold on. (GRUNTS)

261
00:15:26,583 --> 00:15:28,916
(SOMBER CHORAL MUSIC PLAYING)

262
00:15:33,583 --> 00:15:36,083
-(QUEEN MARLENA PANTING)
-(EXPLOSIONS CONTINUE)

263
00:15:38,500 --> 00:15:40,000
MALE VOICE:
The reign of Randor

264
00:15:40,125 --> 00:15:42,666
comes to an end this night.

265
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:45,208
You believed yourself
so strong,

266
00:15:45,333 --> 00:15:48,250
you stopped fearing
what lurked in the shadows.

267
00:15:49,291 --> 00:15:50,875
It was me.

268
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,541
-(STAFF THUDS)
-(GROWLS)

269
00:15:52,666 --> 00:15:54,333
I lurked.

270
00:15:54,916 --> 00:15:59,083
In the deepest and darkest
corners of the universe,

271
00:15:59,208 --> 00:16:01,541
I lurked.

272
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:04,583
But now
I step into the light...

273
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:10,750
so you shall
look upon your downfall.

274
00:16:11,416 --> 00:16:13,000
Go. Don't look back.

275
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:17,750
Adam, don't worry, my boy.
I have you.

276
00:16:20,291 --> 00:16:21,875
Be strong, son.
I'll hold them.

277
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,000
-(WHIMPERS)
-ADAM: Dad?

278
00:16:23,125 --> 00:16:25,500
-KING RANDOR: Go!
-(PANTING)

279
00:16:27,291 --> 00:16:28,416
ADAM: Dad!

280
00:16:28,708 --> 00:16:30,958
(SOMBER CHORAL MUSIC PLAYING)

281
00:16:34,291 --> 00:16:36,041
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

282
00:16:37,208 --> 00:16:39,208
(ALL GRUNTING)

283
00:16:51,208 --> 00:16:52,916
(GROWLS)

284
00:16:53,458 --> 00:16:55,041
(STRAINING)

285
00:16:55,625 --> 00:16:56,666
(SHOUTS)

286
00:16:59,208 --> 00:17:00,666
(STRAINS)

287
00:17:01,041 --> 00:17:03,125
(GROANING)

288
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:06,041
What will you do to me,
you fiend?

289
00:17:06,208 --> 00:17:08,916
I'm only going to cut off
your head.

290
00:17:09,041 --> 00:17:10,125
(GRUNTS)

291
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:15,875
(PANICKED SHOUTING)

292
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:17,708
(LAUGHS MOCKINGLY)

293
00:17:17,833 --> 00:17:21,958
No matter my fate,
Eternos will never be yours.

294
00:17:22,125 --> 00:17:26,041
Your palace is nothing
but brick and glass.

295
00:17:26,208 --> 00:17:28,416
Your crown, a costume.

296
00:17:29,125 --> 00:17:30,208
Mm?

297
00:17:31,083 --> 00:17:33,708
No, I want the power
behind it.

298
00:17:33,833 --> 00:17:34,833
(KNUCKLES CRACK)

299
00:17:35,958 --> 00:17:37,250
Evil-Lyn?

300
00:17:39,708 --> 00:17:41,166
Oh, Evil-Lyn.

301
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:45,166
Well said, Lord Skeletor.
Poetry.

302
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:47,583
Take him away.
His day is done.

303
00:17:47,708 --> 00:17:48,708
(GRUNTS)

304
00:17:48,833 --> 00:17:50,333
With a new dawn,

305
00:17:50,500 --> 00:17:53,916
Eternia shall witness my rise.

306
00:17:54,041 --> 00:17:55,875
-(THUNDER RUMBLES)
-(GROWLS)

307
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:58,375
(LAUGHING WICKEDLY)

308
00:18:02,208 --> 00:18:04,500
(LAUGHTER CONTINUES)

309
00:18:06,125 --> 00:18:07,250
(SNARLS SOFTLY)

310
00:18:08,166 --> 00:18:09,375
(SKELETOR CLEARS THROAT)

311
00:18:12,750 --> 00:18:13,750
(SIGHS)

312
00:18:14,958 --> 00:18:17,250
-That's it. I finished.
-Of course, my Lord.

313
00:18:17,416 --> 00:18:18,583
When I raise my fist
like that,

314
00:18:18,708 --> 00:18:19,708
-I'm done.
-Yes.

315
00:18:19,833 --> 00:18:22,791
That is the crescendo!

316
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:24,791
We'll know
for the future, my Lord.

317
00:18:24,958 --> 00:18:26,416
(BOTH PANTING)

318
00:18:32,958 --> 00:18:33,958
QUEEN MARLENA: They're coming.

319
00:18:35,458 --> 00:18:36,625
Grayskull will fall.

320
00:18:36,791 --> 00:18:39,083
No, it will endure.

321
00:18:39,708 --> 00:18:41,250
Bring the Sword to me, child.

322
00:18:44,375 --> 00:18:45,833
Yes. Now hurry.

323
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:48,833
(EPIC ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

324
00:18:54,916 --> 00:18:56,916
(MUSIC INTENSIFIES)

325
00:19:06,875 --> 00:19:09,458
(CRACKLING)

326
00:19:09,875 --> 00:19:11,833
SORCERESS: You must
take the Sword somewhere safe,

327
00:19:12,625 --> 00:19:14,250
somewhere far away from here.

328
00:19:17,791 --> 00:19:20,166
Then let it be a place
they will never find him.

329
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:21,625
My home.

330
00:19:23,916 --> 00:19:25,541
(PORTAL WHIRS)

331
00:19:29,875 --> 00:19:32,750
Adam, you be safe...
(BREATHING RAGGEDLY)

332
00:19:33,916 --> 00:19:36,083
and never forget
where you came from.

333
00:19:38,375 --> 00:19:40,416
That sword is mine.

334
00:19:43,375 --> 00:19:44,958
Be a good lad
and bring it to me.

335
00:19:45,125 --> 00:19:47,541
Don't you dare
come one step closer.

336
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:49,541
-(GRUNTS)
-(GROANS)

337
00:19:51,333 --> 00:19:52,333
Mom.

338
00:19:52,541 --> 00:19:55,166
Oh, darling, I dare.

339
00:19:55,541 --> 00:19:59,333
Do not lose the Sword.
It's your only way home.

340
00:20:00,416 --> 00:20:02,291
You carry the hope of Eternia.

341
00:20:03,458 --> 00:20:04,625
Now go!

342
00:20:07,958 --> 00:20:09,625
(EPIC MUSIC PLAYING)

343
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:11,625
-(GRUNTS)
-(CRACKLING)

344
00:20:14,250 --> 00:20:15,250
(BIRD SCREAMS)

345
00:20:15,416 --> 00:20:17,458
-SORCERESS: Go!
-(GRUNTS)

346
00:20:17,833 --> 00:20:19,916
(YELPING)

347
00:20:22,083 --> 00:20:24,083
(GRUNTING AND STRAINING)

348
00:20:27,958 --> 00:20:29,666
No!

349
00:20:29,958 --> 00:20:31,958
(CRACKLING)

350
00:20:36,416 --> 00:20:38,541
(ADAM SCREAMS)

351
00:20:41,208 --> 00:20:44,625
ADAM: <i>Anyway,</i>
<i>that's how I ended up in</i>

352
00:20:45,083 --> 00:20:46,625
Oklahoma City.

353
00:20:47,958 --> 00:20:49,708
What about you, Julie?

354
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:51,583
Is your family
from around here?

355
00:20:53,583 --> 00:20:56,750
I'm sorry,
did you say "Skeletor"?

356
00:20:57,416 --> 00:20:59,416
Yeah. Yeah, I did.

357
00:20:59,583 --> 00:21:00,666
Yeah.

358
00:21:01,166 --> 00:21:04,208
Okay, um, I have to take this.

359
00:21:05,375 --> 00:21:07,250
You're ph... It didn't ring.

360
00:21:07,375 --> 00:21:09,125
No, I have to take it
and leave.

361
00:21:09,666 --> 00:21:12,083
Oh, okay, Julie, I'm...
I'm sorry.

362
00:21:12,458 --> 00:21:16,875
I know it sounds crazy.
Was it the sword thing?

363
00:21:18,208 --> 00:21:21,500
The Sword is actually just
a vessel to hold the Power.

364
00:21:22,041 --> 00:21:25,041
Like, uh, it could be this
cup, for example, you know?

365
00:21:25,708 --> 00:21:28,625
So now your cup is holding
the Power of Grayskull,

366
00:21:28,750 --> 00:21:30,541
except it's not your cup,

367
00:21:30,708 --> 00:21:33,583
it was my sword,
and I lost it that night.

368
00:21:33,750 --> 00:21:36,958
You know, I'm not proud
of that. But I lost it and...

369
00:21:37,583 --> 00:21:39,875
(SIGHS) I'm going to find it.

370
00:21:40,041 --> 00:21:43,500
And when I do, it is going
to show me the way home.

371
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:44,958
(SIGHS)

372
00:21:46,458 --> 00:21:48,458
(MUSIC PLAYING FAINTLY)

373
00:21:49,958 --> 00:21:51,000
(SIGHS)

374
00:21:52,708 --> 00:21:53,750
(CRUNCHES)

375
00:21:54,375 --> 00:21:56,333
<i>Are you breaking up with me?</i>

376
00:21:56,541 --> 00:22:00,000
No! But they belong together.

377
00:22:00,166 --> 00:22:01,458
ALLIE: <i>I see.</i>

378
00:22:03,166 --> 00:22:05,416
<i>-Please don't do this.</i>
-(DOORKNOB RATTLING)

379
00:22:05,541 --> 00:22:06,708
<i>-You don't mean it.</i>
-(CLEARS THROAT)

380
00:22:06,833 --> 00:22:08,750
Hey! (CLEARS THROAT)

381
00:22:08,875 --> 00:22:11,000
What's up, brother?
Um... (SNIFFLES)

382
00:22:11,500 --> 00:22:12,791
You're... You're home early.

383
00:22:13,291 --> 00:22:14,291
I don't want to talk about it.

384
00:22:15,083 --> 00:22:16,083
Oh.

385
00:22:16,750 --> 00:22:17,833
Dude.

386
00:22:18,541 --> 00:22:22,000
You told her?
Like, the whole thing?

387
00:22:22,166 --> 00:22:24,541
Sorceress,
the talking green tiger?

388
00:22:24,750 --> 00:22:26,125
Even the king dude's
crushing disappointment

389
00:22:26,250 --> 00:22:27,541
in your lack of masculinity?

390
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:31,500
Yeah, yeah, I probably
should've left that part out.

391
00:22:31,708 --> 00:22:33,166
I mean, you tell
some girl from Hinge

392
00:22:33,291 --> 00:22:34,500
that you're
from another planet,

393
00:22:34,666 --> 00:22:36,083
but you're stuck here
till you find

394
00:22:36,208 --> 00:22:38,833
this magic sword
that's going to get you home.

395
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:41,083
It just makes you sound
a little...

396
00:22:42,125 --> 00:22:43,541
very crazy.

397
00:22:44,208 --> 00:22:45,500
The drawings
of the ripped dudes,

398
00:22:45,625 --> 00:22:46,625
the stories you're telling...

399
00:22:46,750 --> 00:22:48,375
They're ripped in real life,
dude, okay?

400
00:22:48,541 --> 00:22:50,541
Like, she asks me
where I'm from,

401
00:22:50,666 --> 00:22:52,291
like, what am I supposed
to say?

402
00:22:52,458 --> 00:22:53,791
That your parents were killed

403
00:22:53,916 --> 00:22:55,416
in some sort
of a traumatic event.

404
00:22:55,583 --> 00:22:56,583
I'm so sorry, by the way.

405
00:22:56,708 --> 00:22:58,541
And that
you're blocking it out

406
00:22:58,666 --> 00:23:00,000
and you're replacing it
with this fantasy.

407
00:23:00,166 --> 00:23:01,791
Like, isn't that what
your therapist says?

408
00:23:01,958 --> 00:23:04,791
You're saying that I should
just forget who I am?

409
00:23:04,958 --> 00:23:07,708
My... My entire
life's purpose?

410
00:23:07,875 --> 00:23:09,458
Maybe your
entire life's purpose

411
00:23:09,583 --> 00:23:11,041
is just to not be weird.

412
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:13,416
You ever think about that?

413
00:23:13,583 --> 00:23:16,041
Like, why can't you
just go to work,

414
00:23:16,166 --> 00:23:18,083
pay your rent,
live for the weekend,

415
00:23:18,250 --> 00:23:20,416
and count the days
till your next vacation?

416
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:24,541
Just like everyone else.

417
00:23:33,500 --> 00:23:34,833
-(SWITCH CLICKS)
-(SIGHS)

418
00:23:35,541 --> 00:23:37,833
(WISTFUL PIANO MUSIC PLAYING)

419
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:52,750
The assignment was draw your
favorite historical figure.

420
00:23:54,791 --> 00:23:57,083
-(SIGHS)
-Ram Man is historical.

421
00:23:57,208 --> 00:23:58,625
(ALL LAUGH)

422
00:24:20,500 --> 00:24:22,708
(WISTFUL PIANO MUSIC
CONTINUES)

423
00:24:43,916 --> 00:24:44,916
(SIGHS)

424
00:24:45,833 --> 00:24:48,125
(ALARM BUZZING)

425
00:24:50,958 --> 00:24:53,208
(UPBEAT POST-PUNK
SONG PLAYING)

426
00:24:59,541 --> 00:25:00,666
No. (SIGHS)

427
00:25:11,625 --> 00:25:13,500
-(INHALES SHARPLY)
-(TIRES SCREECH)

428
00:25:14,041 --> 00:25:15,000
Nope.

429
00:25:15,208 --> 00:25:16,208
(ENGINE STARTS)

430
00:25:16,333 --> 00:25:17,958
-(ENGINE REVS)
-(TIRES SCREECH)

431
00:25:20,041 --> 00:25:21,708
It's going to be a good day.

432
00:25:21,833 --> 00:25:22,958
(SIGHS)

433
00:25:23,083 --> 00:25:26,166
WOMAN 1: <i>I hear you</i>
<i>emotionally,</i>

434
00:25:26,333 --> 00:25:29,833
I feel you consensually,

435
00:25:30,250 --> 00:25:33,916
I see you
for who you really are.

436
00:25:34,083 --> 00:25:35,750
And you can
remind yourself of that

437
00:25:35,875 --> 00:25:37,750
with our favorite mantra.

438
00:25:37,916 --> 00:25:40,625
Let's all get up
and say it together.

439
00:25:40,791 --> 00:25:42,708
Let's all get up, okay.

440
00:25:43,166 --> 00:25:48,166
ALL: I have the power to be
the best version of myself.

441
00:25:50,708 --> 00:25:54,000
WOMAN 2: It might be his
truth, but it's not my truth.

442
00:25:54,166 --> 00:25:56,000
I think we all need
to be aligned

443
00:25:56,125 --> 00:25:59,166
{\an8}on whose truth
we're talking about here.

444
00:25:59,916 --> 00:26:01,583
ADAM: I feel... I feel like
what's happening

445
00:26:01,750 --> 00:26:03,375
is there's a lot
of truth-talking going on,

446
00:26:03,541 --> 00:26:05,750
but maybe what would
be more constructive

447
00:26:05,916 --> 00:26:09,125
is a little bit
of truth-listening. Right?

448
00:26:10,208 --> 00:26:11,583
I'm sorry, what?

449
00:26:13,208 --> 00:26:14,208
(STRAINING)

450
00:26:15,625 --> 00:26:17,416
(GRUNTING)

451
00:26:17,541 --> 00:26:18,750
(CLUNKS)

452
00:26:22,666 --> 00:26:24,166
-(STRAINS)
-You're in my spot.

453
00:26:24,333 --> 00:26:25,958
-What?
-(GRUNTS)

454
00:26:26,083 --> 00:26:27,916
-You're taking my spot.
-Oh, I'm... Um...

455
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:30,000
I'm sorry.

456
00:26:32,125 --> 00:26:33,125
(MAN EXHALES)

457
00:26:35,541 --> 00:26:38,208
Uh, hey,
any advice for a new guy?

458
00:26:38,791 --> 00:26:41,791
You know, like,
some words of wisdom.

459
00:26:42,083 --> 00:26:46,333
All right, kid, you got to get
behind yourself, not in front.

460
00:26:47,166 --> 00:26:50,791
The front's a facade.
But you back yourself?

461
00:26:52,250 --> 00:26:54,208
There's nothing
you can't achieve.

462
00:26:55,875 --> 00:26:56,875
Cool.

463
00:26:58,625 --> 00:27:01,416
Really cool. Um...

464
00:27:01,833 --> 00:27:04,583
Could you just run me through
that, like, one more time?

465
00:27:04,750 --> 00:27:06,583
No. That's all you get.

466
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:09,000
(SIGHS)

467
00:27:13,208 --> 00:27:14,625
Good journey, kid.

468
00:27:18,333 --> 00:27:20,333
(UPBEAT SONG CONTINUES)

469
00:27:21,166 --> 00:27:22,583
(TYPING)

470
00:27:25,583 --> 00:27:26,958
(SNIFFS)

471
00:27:34,416 --> 00:27:36,125
-Ding-dong. (LAUGHS)
-(GASPS)

472
00:27:38,083 --> 00:27:39,416
-Oh, hey.
-Hi.

473
00:27:39,541 --> 00:27:41,500
Um, do you have
a moment to come

474
00:27:41,625 --> 00:27:42,791
talk to me
in my office real quick?

475
00:27:42,958 --> 00:27:46,583
Uh, I was actually doing
some super important HR stuff.

476
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:48,333
I can see that. Yeah.

477
00:27:48,458 --> 00:27:50,500
Um, but I wasn't
really asking.

478
00:27:50,625 --> 00:27:51,875
I was more telling you. So...

479
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:53,375
-(CHUCKLES)
-Oh, okay.

480
00:27:53,541 --> 00:27:55,750
Yeah, it's confusing. Like,
the tone's a little confusing.

481
00:27:55,916 --> 00:27:57,375
It's like, is it a question
or not? It's not.

482
00:27:57,541 --> 00:27:58,583
-So, I will see you...
-Okay.

483
00:27:58,708 --> 00:27:59,750
...in, like, 10 minutes? Okay.

484
00:27:59,916 --> 00:28:01,125
Okay, Suzie.

485
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:06,125
(SIGHS)

486
00:28:10,333 --> 00:28:15,333
Adam, do you ever think about
your future at this company?

487
00:28:15,875 --> 00:28:17,083
I... Should I?

488
00:28:17,333 --> 00:28:18,708
(CHUCKLES) Okay,

489
00:28:18,833 --> 00:28:21,583
let me try to slide in there
from a different angle. Um...

490
00:28:22,666 --> 00:28:23,833
You're good at your job.

491
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:27,583
You're friendly,
honest, thoughtful.

492
00:28:27,750 --> 00:28:31,041
People listen to you.
People like you.

493
00:28:31,583 --> 00:28:32,666
But...

494
00:28:32,833 --> 00:28:34,916
you seem distracted,

495
00:28:35,083 --> 00:28:37,916
and I don't ever
want to harsh anyone's buzz.

496
00:28:38,083 --> 00:28:40,541
And if your buzz is nerd stuff
and sword things,

497
00:28:40,666 --> 00:28:42,666
that is awesomesauce.

498
00:28:42,833 --> 00:28:44,958
But I wouldn't
be doing my part

499
00:28:45,083 --> 00:28:47,333
if I didn't give you
this little ream job here.

500
00:28:48,375 --> 00:28:49,375
"Ream job"?

501
00:28:50,166 --> 00:28:52,041
Talking-to. You know?

502
