(BREATHES HEAVILY)

1262
01:07:11,708 --> 01:07:13,041
-(GRUNTS)
-Whoa!

1263
01:07:13,166 --> 01:07:14,583
-What the...?
-(PANTS)

1264
01:07:14,708 --> 01:07:16,000
-(SKY SLED POWERS DOWN)
-Okay.

1265
01:07:16,125 --> 01:07:17,291
(POWERING UP)

1266
01:07:18,083 --> 01:07:19,083
Yeah.

1267
01:07:20,208 --> 01:07:22,458
(SCREAMING)

1268
01:07:28,000 --> 01:07:29,083
Whoa!

1269
01:07:29,208 --> 01:07:31,083
(STRAINING)

1270
01:07:37,583 --> 01:07:38,583
(STRAINS)

1271
01:07:46,750 --> 01:07:49,041
-(WHIRRING)
-(CRACKLING)

1272
01:07:53,375 --> 01:07:54,375
DUNCAN: Whoa!

1273
01:07:57,583 --> 01:07:59,208
(LASERS FIRING)

1274
01:08:01,541 --> 01:08:02,625
TEELA: We're losing altitude.

1275
01:08:02,750 --> 01:08:03,916
You know,
if you put less pressure

1276
01:08:04,041 --> 01:08:05,833
-on the yoke, you'll get...
-Not one word.

1277
01:08:05,958 --> 01:08:07,291
(LASERS FIRING)

1278
01:08:12,916 --> 01:08:14,291
(ENGINE ROARING)

1279
01:08:14,416 --> 01:08:16,333
(SCREAMING)

1280
01:08:18,083 --> 01:08:19,958
(SCREAMING)

1281
01:08:21,041 --> 01:08:22,500
(GASPING)

1282
01:08:25,666 --> 01:08:26,875
(SCREAMS IN CRACKED VOICE)

1283
01:08:32,041 --> 01:08:33,625
(STRAINS)

1284
01:08:38,708 --> 01:08:40,000
(SCREAMS)

1285
01:08:41,625 --> 01:08:43,416
(SCREAMS)

1286
01:08:45,166 --> 01:08:46,208
(THUD)

1287
01:08:50,958 --> 01:08:51,958
(GLASS SQUEAKS)

1288
01:08:54,833 --> 01:08:56,125
(GRUNTS)

1289
01:08:56,250 --> 01:08:58,666
-(EPIC ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)
-(GROANS)

1290
01:09:05,416 --> 01:09:06,416
We're not going to make it.

1291
01:09:06,541 --> 01:09:08,791
Teela, hold her
as steady as you can.

1292
01:09:08,916 --> 01:09:10,291
Oh, says the drunk guy.

1293
01:09:12,958 --> 01:09:14,000
Whoa!

1294
01:09:14,125 --> 01:09:15,708
(GRUNTS) Whoa.

1295
01:09:16,750 --> 01:09:17,958
(EXCLAIMS)

1296
01:09:18,083 --> 01:09:19,625
(PANTING)

1297
01:09:24,916 --> 01:09:25,916
All right.

1298
01:09:28,916 --> 01:09:30,041
(WEAPON POWERING UP)

1299
01:09:33,916 --> 01:09:34,916
Adam?

1300
01:09:37,250 --> 01:09:38,375
(CHUCKLES)

1301
01:09:38,500 --> 01:09:40,208
Adam! Hey!

1302
01:09:40,333 --> 01:09:43,125
Hey, look out behind you!

1303
01:09:47,708 --> 01:09:50,000
-Get out of there, you moron.
-What?

1304
01:09:50,125 --> 01:09:51,666
(ACCELERATING)

1305
01:09:53,208 --> 01:09:54,208
You're going to die.

1306
01:09:57,291 --> 01:09:58,750
(CRACKLING)

1307
01:09:59,458 --> 01:10:00,458
(PANTS)

1308
01:10:01,208 --> 01:10:03,291
(SHOUTING)

1309
01:10:04,250 --> 01:10:05,708
(SHIP THUDS)

1310
01:10:06,375 --> 01:10:07,375
(GROANS)

1311
01:10:08,125 --> 01:10:09,791
(WHIRRING)

1312
01:10:16,125 --> 01:10:17,125
(GROWLS)

1313
01:10:17,250 --> 01:10:18,500
(YELLS)

1314
01:10:20,250 --> 01:10:21,708
(PANTING)

1315
01:10:23,833 --> 01:10:25,375
(GRUNTS)

1316
01:10:26,750 --> 01:10:29,083
(SHOUTS)

1317
01:10:38,125 --> 01:10:39,583
(ENGINE WHINING)

1318
01:10:41,916 --> 01:10:42,916
(YELLS)

1319
01:10:45,750 --> 01:10:46,750
(GRUNTS)

1320
01:10:50,250 --> 01:10:52,208
(GRUNTING)

1321
01:10:53,208 --> 01:10:54,208
(GROANS)

1322
01:10:54,333 --> 01:10:56,166
-(SCRAPING)
-(ENGINE POWERING DOWN)

1323
01:11:01,916 --> 01:11:04,250
Wow, you can really fly.

1324
01:11:04,375 --> 01:11:06,000
(PANTING)

1325
01:11:06,125 --> 01:11:07,666
I don't want to hear it.

1326
01:11:09,000 --> 01:11:11,208
SKELETOR: Insurgents
of Eternia.

1327
01:11:11,791 --> 01:11:14,666
Your long reprieve
has come to an end.

1328
01:11:14,791 --> 01:11:17,208
You are done.

1329
01:11:17,333 --> 01:11:18,458
(CAPTIVES WHIMPER)

1330
01:11:19,416 --> 01:11:21,791
Well, if you would live
to see another morning,

1331
01:11:22,291 --> 01:11:25,333
I now demand your fealty.

1332
01:11:26,041 --> 01:11:28,541
Do you know
what that means, miscreant?

1333
01:11:29,625 --> 01:11:34,083
It means I shall kill you
one by one

1334
01:11:34,208 --> 01:11:38,333
until you tell me the name
of that insolent barbarian.

1335
01:11:39,666 --> 01:11:42,166
And do you know who I mean?

1336
01:11:43,208 --> 01:11:46,458
Muscles. Loincloth.
All over tan.

1337
01:11:46,583 --> 01:11:49,125
Big, shiny sword.

1338
01:11:49,250 --> 01:11:50,333
Mm.

1339
01:11:52,208 --> 01:11:53,416
(SIGHS)

1340
01:11:54,500 --> 01:11:55,500
No?

1341
01:11:57,916 --> 01:11:59,916
-Very well.
-(SOFT WHIMPERING)

1342
01:12:02,541 --> 01:12:03,541
(STAFF CLANGS)

1343
01:12:04,958 --> 01:12:06,125
You.

1344
01:12:06,875 --> 01:12:08,916
-Evil-Lyn, who is this?
-EVIL-LYN: Um...

1345
01:12:09,916 --> 01:12:11,750
Moss Man.

1346
01:12:12,250 --> 01:12:13,583
He'll do. Mm.

1347
01:12:13,708 --> 01:12:15,791
-No! No, no.
-(CAPTIVES EXCLAIM)

1348
01:12:16,625 --> 01:12:17,625
(MOSS MAN GROANS)

1349
01:12:17,750 --> 01:12:20,791
Watch,
fallen heroes of Eternia,

1350
01:12:21,291 --> 01:12:24,833
as he begs
for his miserable life.

1351
01:12:26,208 --> 01:12:27,208
Go on.

1352
01:12:27,333 --> 01:12:28,333
(KNUCKLES CRACK)

1353
01:12:28,458 --> 01:12:29,916
Beg.

1354
01:12:30,083 --> 01:12:31,375
No.

1355
01:12:31,500 --> 01:12:33,291
-(SCREAMS)
-No!

1356
01:12:33,416 --> 01:12:35,000
(CAPTIVES WHIMPERING)

1357
01:12:36,875 --> 01:12:39,708
SKELETOR: Oh, look,
darling, I made mulch.

1358
01:12:39,833 --> 01:12:41,791
(LAUGHTER)

1359
01:12:43,041 --> 01:12:45,083
Very good. Mulch.

1360
01:12:45,208 --> 01:12:47,375
(LAUGHTER CONTINUES)

1361
01:12:53,833 --> 01:12:55,208
-(SIGHS)
-(EVIL-LYN CLEARS THROAT)

1362
01:12:56,041 --> 01:12:57,791
So I ask again,

1363
01:12:57,916 --> 01:13:02,208
who is the warrior
who fought for you today?

1364
01:13:02,750 --> 01:13:03,916
FISTO: No more!

1365
01:13:04,041 --> 01:13:05,333
No more. I'll tell.

1366
01:13:05,458 --> 01:13:06,916
Oh, please do.

1367
01:13:07,041 --> 01:13:09,500
It's the young prince,
returned from the dead.

1368
01:13:10,000 --> 01:13:11,000
(GROANS)

1369
01:13:11,500 --> 01:13:12,875
-(CAPTIVES EXCLAIM)
-(GASPS)

1370
01:13:13,000 --> 01:13:14,500
Is it indeed?

1371
01:13:15,125 --> 01:13:17,625
Take them all away.
Lock them up.

1372
01:13:17,750 --> 01:13:20,416
Let this midden burn
to the ground.

1373
01:13:21,458 --> 01:13:22,583
(SPARK HISSES)

1374
01:13:25,250 --> 01:13:27,166
Well, they're not going
to follow us in here.

1375
01:13:28,875 --> 01:13:31,125
Not without reinforcements.

1376
01:13:31,291 --> 01:13:32,833
I'm going to go look for Adam
while there's still light.

1377
01:13:32,958 --> 01:13:34,791
No, no, no, no,
you leave that to me.

1378
01:13:34,958 --> 01:13:37,000
-Really, Dad. I got it.
-Teela. This is what I do.

1379
01:13:38,125 --> 01:13:40,458
Did. This is what you did.

1380
01:13:40,583 --> 01:13:43,250
I am handling this. Stay here.

1381
01:13:52,166 --> 01:13:53,750
(CRICKETS CHIRPING)

1382
01:14:00,500 --> 01:14:01,666
(GRUNTS)

1383
01:14:03,333 --> 01:14:04,500
(BOX THUDS)

1384
01:14:19,500 --> 01:14:20,500
(SCOFFS)

1385
01:14:25,666 --> 01:14:27,666
(WISTFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1386
01:14:34,083 --> 01:14:35,375
(PANTING)

1387
01:14:36,625 --> 01:14:38,125
Where am I?

1388
01:14:38,250 --> 01:14:40,041
(PANTING HEAVILY)

1389
01:14:45,250 --> 01:14:46,291
Who am I?

1390
01:14:46,416 --> 01:14:47,500
SORCERESS: <i>You are he</i>

1391
01:14:47,625 --> 01:14:50,125
<i>who will restore peace</i>
<i>to Eternia.</i> (ECHOING)

1392
01:14:51,458 --> 01:14:54,208
<i>The Champion of Grayskull.</i>

1393
01:14:57,916 --> 01:15:00,333
(ETHEREAL CHORAL
MUSIC PLAYING)

1394
01:15:12,875 --> 01:15:14,250
-TEELA: Adam.
-(SCREECHING)

1395
01:15:17,000 --> 01:15:19,083
(SIGHS) Thank Zodac,
you're alive!

1396
01:15:19,208 --> 01:15:21,125
I think you just
shooed off the Sorceress.

1397
01:15:21,791 --> 01:15:22,833
(SWORD SHEATHES)

1398
01:15:22,958 --> 01:15:24,958
That's not the Sorceress.

1399
01:15:25,375 --> 01:15:27,458
I really think that
that was the Sorceress.

1400
01:15:28,583 --> 01:15:29,583
Sure.

1401
01:15:30,541 --> 01:15:31,541
Are you hurt?

1402
01:15:32,125 --> 01:15:33,583
Weirdly, not at all.

1403
01:15:35,375 --> 01:15:36,375
Good.

1404
01:15:42,291 --> 01:15:44,750
Come on, it's getting dark.

1405
01:15:48,958 --> 01:15:50,333
TEELA:
We'll camp here tonight,

1406
01:15:50,458 --> 01:15:51,875
get moving
first thing tomorrow.

1407
01:15:52,416 --> 01:15:53,875
(DUNCAN GRUNTING)

1408
01:15:59,333 --> 01:16:00,333
What? (CHUCKLES)

1409
01:16:00,833 --> 01:16:04,250
Nothing. Just haven't seen you
like this in a while.

1410
01:16:04,416 --> 01:16:08,500
Well, Man-At-Arms
is in here somewhere.

1411
01:16:09,083 --> 01:16:10,416
I hope you find him.

1412
01:16:11,416 --> 01:16:13,416
Hey, wait a second.

1413
01:16:15,458 --> 01:16:16,791
What have we got here?

1414
01:16:16,916 --> 01:16:18,833
(LAUGHING)

1415
01:16:18,958 --> 01:16:20,833
Oh, who's up for a drink?

1416
01:16:21,083 --> 01:16:23,458
Dad, are you serious?

1417
01:16:23,625 --> 01:16:26,166
What? Come on. Sit down.

1418
01:16:26,333 --> 01:16:27,333
Let's crack open a few.

1419
01:16:27,458 --> 01:16:29,000
Tell some stories,
sing some songs.

1420
01:16:29,166 --> 01:16:31,000
If we don't celebrate
the small victories...

1421
01:16:31,166 --> 01:16:33,541
Victory? What victory?

1422
01:16:33,708 --> 01:16:34,958
Well, we didn't die.

1423
01:16:35,125 --> 01:16:36,541
Oh, that's a victory for you?

1424
01:16:36,708 --> 01:16:38,458
Teela, I say we earned it.

1425
01:16:38,625 --> 01:16:41,083
You've been "earning it"
for 15 years.

1426
01:16:49,666 --> 01:16:52,625
(GROANS) More for you and me.
Come on. Sit down.

1427
01:16:57,875 --> 01:16:59,916
Here's to the return
of the Sword

1428
01:17:00,083 --> 01:17:04,000
and the Champion of Grayskull!
(SNICKERS)

1429
01:17:04,333 --> 01:17:05,541
Ripping some dude's arm off

1430
01:17:05,708 --> 01:17:06,958
doesn't really seem like
the kind of thing

1431
01:17:07,083 --> 01:17:08,291
that we should be celebrating.

1432
01:17:08,791 --> 01:17:10,291
Well, it was you or him.

1433
01:17:10,750 --> 01:17:12,583
Like, whatever happened to...

1434
01:17:12,708 --> 01:17:16,375
to understanding
and listening?

1435
01:17:17,416 --> 01:17:18,541
Just talking to one another?

1436
01:17:18,708 --> 01:17:19,958
Oh, talk.

1437
01:17:20,125 --> 01:17:21,916
What are you going to do
when a guy charges

1438
01:17:22,041 --> 01:17:23,666
towards your family
with a sword?

1439
01:17:23,833 --> 01:17:25,416
Okay, I get it.
What I'm supposed to say...?

1440
01:17:25,541 --> 01:17:26,541
You... You fight him, right?

1441
01:17:26,666 --> 01:17:29,208
No, you protect them.

1442
01:17:29,375 --> 01:17:31,708
You... You're thinking
about it all wrong.

1443
01:17:31,875 --> 01:17:33,583
I mean, you scoff
at the trigger-happy grunts!

1444
01:17:33,708 --> 01:17:35,041
Look how backward
they all are.

1445
01:17:35,166 --> 01:17:36,458
But when the war breaks out,

1446
01:17:36,583 --> 01:17:38,166
it's not the poets
that step up.

1447
01:17:38,333 --> 01:17:39,875
It's the man with the muscle.

1448
01:17:40,041 --> 01:17:41,958
And he's not doing it
for glory.

1449
01:17:45,583 --> 01:17:47,041
He's doing it so his...

1450
01:17:48,375 --> 01:17:50,708
his children can see
another morning.

1451
01:17:50,875 --> 01:17:53,708
That is a man,
as far as I can tell.

1452
01:17:54,416 --> 01:17:57,041
He stands up
when he is needed.

1453
01:17:58,958 --> 01:18:00,041
Like you did.

1454
01:18:01,708 --> 01:18:02,833
Speaking of which,

1455
01:18:03,000 --> 01:18:06,875
you, uh...
you weren't bad earlier on.

1456
01:18:07,000 --> 01:18:08,208
(CHUCKLES)

1457
01:18:10,291 --> 01:18:13,208
That's the nicest thing
you've ever said to me.

1458
01:18:13,375 --> 01:18:15,458
I mean, your form,
it's a little shoddy.

1459
01:18:15,625 --> 01:18:17,875
And your technique
could do some work.

1460
01:18:18,041 --> 01:18:19,958
-But, uh, not bad.
-There he is.

1461
01:18:20,125 --> 01:18:22,000
There's the Duncan I remember.

1462
01:18:23,041 --> 01:18:25,166
-(LAUGHING)
-Um, good.

1463
01:18:41,916 --> 01:18:43,000
(SIGHS)

1464
01:18:43,833 --> 01:18:46,875
Hey, can you come
help me with this?

1465
01:18:52,291 --> 01:18:54,291
-(SHIP CREAKS)
-(ADAM GRUNTS)

1466
01:18:56,291 --> 01:18:57,375
Whoa.

1467
01:18:58,958 --> 01:18:59,958
It is quite heavy,

1468
01:19:00,083 --> 01:19:01,291
-so if you could just...
-Oh, my God! Yeah.

1469
01:19:01,875 --> 01:19:03,416
-Yeah.
-(TEELA GRUNTS)

1470
01:19:03,541 --> 01:19:05,000
Your, um... (CLEARS THROAT)

1471
01:19:05,125 --> 01:19:06,458
-Your loincloth is in my...
-(BLOWS)

1472
01:19:06,583 --> 01:19:07,875
-Sorry.
-Fine.

1473
01:19:09,250 --> 01:19:10,291
(TEELA GRUNTS)

1474
01:19:11,208 --> 01:19:13,708
-(SHIP CLANGS)
-(ADAM BREATHING HEAVILY)

1475
01:19:19,375 --> 01:19:24,291
So, how does it feel
to be the mighty warrior?

1476
01:19:25,541 --> 01:19:26,791
ADAM: Uh...

1477
01:19:29,125 --> 01:19:34,416
All things considered, I feel
pretty great. (CHUCKLES)

1478
01:19:34,541 --> 01:19:36,500
I'm not quite sure what
happened to my shirt though.

1479
01:19:36,625 --> 01:19:38,916
(INHALES SHARPLY) Or my pants.

1480
01:19:39,416 --> 01:19:41,375
Do those come back,

1481
01:19:41,500 --> 01:19:43,625
or do I have to buy
a new pair every time?

1482
01:19:44,416 --> 01:19:46,041
I really missed you, you know.

1483
01:19:47,875 --> 01:19:48,875
Me too.

1484
01:19:51,750 --> 01:19:55,083
I thought about you.
All the time.

1485
01:19:59,375 --> 01:20:00,375
Me too.

1486
01:20:02,458 --> 01:20:04,333
Honestly,
there wasn't a day went by

1487
01:20:04,458 --> 01:20:05,708
I didn't think about you.

1488
01:20:05,833 --> 01:20:07,083
(ROMANTIC MUSIC BUILDING)

1489
01:20:07,208 --> 01:20:08,208
Me too.

1490
01:20:10,000 --> 01:20:11,500
And how much...

1491
01:20:13,291 --> 01:20:15,083
our friendship means to me.

1492
01:20:15,458 --> 01:20:16,500
(MUSIC STOPS)

1493
01:20:16,625 --> 01:20:17,708
ADAM: Hmm?

1494
01:20:17,833 --> 01:20:19,375
You were always
such a good friend.

1495
01:20:19,541 --> 01:20:21,166
Like a really,
really good friend. You know,

1496
01:20:21,291 --> 01:20:22,958
-practically a little brother.
-Hmm.

1497
01:20:23,083 --> 01:20:24,625
Yeah. You've always
been my friend

1498
01:20:24,750 --> 01:20:26,333
and you'll always
be my friend.

1499
01:20:26,500 --> 01:20:27,958
And nothing will change that.
Not ever.

1500
01:20:28,083 --> 01:20:30,833
-(BOTH LAUGH AWKWARDLY)
-My dawg. Whew!

1501
01:20:30,958 --> 01:20:31,958
-Phew, I know. Okay.
-Yeah.

1502
01:20:32,083 --> 01:20:33,125
-All right.
-Weight off of me.

1503
01:20:33,250 --> 01:20:34,458
Well, let's go
confiscate that flask

1504
01:20:34,583 --> 01:20:35,750
before my dad starts singing.

1505
01:20:36,291 --> 01:20:38,125
Yeah, we don't...
we don't want that.

1506
01:20:38,291 --> 01:20:39,625
-TEELA: Yeah.
-We...

1507
01:20:43,625 --> 01:20:46,333
(RUMBLING)

1508
01:20:48,500 --> 01:20:50,375
(SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

1509
01:20:50,500 --> 01:20:54,083
Behold insignificant wretches,
it is I,

1510
01:20:54,750 --> 01:20:56,208
Skeletor.

1511
01:20:56,750 --> 01:21:01,500
And you are but worms
beneath my feet.

1512
01:21:01,666 --> 01:21:04,916
Butt-worms?
He just called us butt-worms.

1513
01:21:05,375 --> 01:21:06,750
SKELETOR: Yet there is one
among you

1514
01:21:06,875 --> 01:21:08,708
who thinks
he has a higher purpose.

1515
01:21:08,875 --> 01:21:12,833
It seems the prodigal prince
has returned.

1516
01:21:13,000 --> 01:21:16,750
But this is not your Eternia
anymore, Prince Adam.

1517
01:21:17,583 --> 01:21:21,125
It is mine.
And so is everything in it.

1518
01:21:21,791 --> 01:21:24,250
Including that sword
you carry,

1519
01:21:24,416 --> 01:21:28,250
for it is fit for a far
mightier hand than yours.

1520
01:21:29,583 --> 01:21:33,541
So, here
is my magnanimous offer.

1521
01:21:33,708 --> 01:21:36,333
Bring the Sword of Power to me
at Snake Mountain

1522
01:21:36,500 --> 01:21:39,875
and you might yet
be reconciled with your...

1523
01:21:40,041 --> 01:21:42,708
mummy and daddy.

1524
01:21:42,833 --> 01:21:46,750
-(BREATHING HEAVILY)
-Yes, they're alive and well.

1525
01:21:47,625 --> 01:21:51,416
Okay, not "well,"
but they're alive.

1526
01:21:53,041 --> 01:21:57,416
Imagine, you could be
a happy family together again.

1527
01:21:59,000 --> 01:22:01,833
Or they could die...

1528
01:22:02,000 --> 01:22:03,000
horribly.

1529
01:22:04,333 --> 01:22:07,666
And that will forever
be on you.

1530
01:22:08,625 --> 01:22:12,375
Oh, how heavy will that sword
weigh in your hand then,

1531
01:22:13,041 --> 01:22:14,958
Champion of Grayskull?

1532
01:22:16,000 --> 01:22:18,000
(SKELETOR SNICKERING)

1533
01:22:18,125 --> 01:22:20,375
(LAUGHING WICKEDLY)

1534
01:22:26,333 --> 01:22:27,625
I have to leave.

1535
01:22:28,500 --> 01:22:29,500
Now.

1536
01:22:29,875 --> 01:22:32,416
Adam! Adam! It's a trap!

1537
01:22:33,000 --> 01:22:34,625
We can't let Skeletor
get his hands on the Sword.

1538
01:22:34,750 --> 01:22:35,750
He'd be unstoppable.

1539
01:22:35,875 --> 01:22:37,666
I'm not going
to give him the Sword.

1540
01:22:37,791 --> 01:22:39,000
I'm going to kill him with it.

1541
01:22:39,291 --> 01:22:40,625
TEELA: This is Skeletor
we're talking about.

1542
01:22:40,750 --> 01:22:41,875
You can't just charge
into this.

1543
01:22:42,208 --> 01:22:45,708
(RAISES VOICE) I have the
power of a god in my hands.

1544
01:22:45,875 --> 01:22:49,333
But you are not a god.
You're a man.

1545
01:22:49,500 --> 01:22:51,250
He took my family, Teela!

1546
01:22:53,041 --> 01:22:54,208
I have to save them.

1547
01:22:56,958 --> 01:22:59,458
It's what a man does, right?

1548
01:23:00,041 --> 01:23:03,125
(SCOFFS)
You sound like my dad.

1549
01:23:03,791 --> 01:23:04,916
Is that a bad thing?

1550
01:23:05,083 --> 01:23:06,791
-We'll see.
-DUNCAN: Hey!

1551
01:23:07,375 --> 01:23:09,208
I'm going with you
or without you.

1552
01:23:10,541 --> 01:23:11,541
DUNCAN: Adam.

1553
01:23:14,041 --> 01:23:15,083
We're with you.

1554
01:23:19,958 --> 01:23:21,208
Every step of the way.

1555
01:23:23,083 --> 01:23:25,250
ROBOTO: It's like
they want to die all the time.

1556
01:23:25,416 --> 01:23:26,416
Not now.

1557
01:23:32,166 --> 01:23:33,166
ADAM: Come on.

1558
01:23:34,125 --> 01:23:35,833
Snake Mountain is this way.

1559
01:23:36,708 --> 01:23:39,333
-(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)
-(FALCON CALLS)

1560
01:23:45,125 --> 01:23:46,750
(SCREECHES)

1561
01:24:14,416 --> 01:24:16,000
DUNCAN: We don't know
what's in there.

1562
01:24:17,166 --> 01:24:18,250
I'm in there.

1563
01:24:23,000 --> 01:24:24,250
Follow my lead.

1564
01:24:27,541 --> 01:24:28,875
Ho the...

1565
01:24:29,000 --> 01:24:30,291
Uh... (CLEARS THROAT)

1566
01:24:30,416 --> 01:24:33,291
Hi, I am Adam.

1567
01:24:34,208 --> 01:24:35,750
Prince of Eternia

1568
01:24:35,875 --> 01:24:38,458
and defender of the secrets
of Castle Grayskull.

1569
01:24:39,250 --> 01:24:41,375
And I carry with me
the Sword of Power.

1570
01:24:43,208 --> 01:24:45,625
-(GOAT MAN GROWLS SOFTLY)
-(AXE THUDS)

1571
01:24:46,750 --> 01:24:49,291
Surrender your weapon to me.

1572
01:24:49,458 --> 01:24:53,958
I will give the Sword
to Skeletor and Skeletor only.

1573
01:24:54,083 --> 01:24:56,208
-(LAUGHS)
-ADAM: Hmm.

1574
01:24:56,916 --> 01:24:58,291
Keep the Sword.

1575
01:24:58,583 --> 01:24:59,583
Guards!

1576
01:25:00,291 --> 01:25:01,375
Ah.

1577
01:25:01,500 --> 01:25:03,458
(GUARDS GRUNTING)

1578
01:25:05,791 --> 01:25:08,208
(GATE CLANKING, THUDS)

1579
01:25:10,416 --> 01:25:16,208
Take this one and his gorgeous
muscles to Lord Skeletor.

1580
01:25:17,250 --> 01:25:19,000
The rest will come with me.

1581
01:25:19,500 --> 01:25:21,166
-Prepare the dungeons.
-(GUARDS GRUNT)

1582
01:25:22,916 --> 01:25:24,500
-Adam, you give him hell!
-(GUARD GRUNTS)

1583
01:25:31,250 --> 01:25:33,291
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

1584
01:25:42,625 --> 01:25:44,333
(GOAT MAN SNARLS)

1585
01:25:46,000 --> 01:25:47,000
(AXE THUDS)

1586
01:25:49,250 --> 01:25:50,375
(SNARLS)

1587
01:26:11,333 --> 01:26:14,166
SKELETOR: Killer view,
isn't it?

1588
01:26:18,583 --> 01:26:20,000
(GASPING SOFTLY)

1589
01:26:21,541 --> 01:26:23,541
Shall I give you two a moment?

1590
01:26:24,916 --> 01:26:25,916
Dad?

1591
01:26:26,833 --> 01:26:28,125
Adam?

1592
01:26:29,041 --> 01:26:30,541
Is it you?

1593
01:26:30,791 --> 01:26:31,875
Yeah.

1594
01:26:33,458 --> 01:26:34,541
It's me.

1595
01:26:34,916 --> 01:26:37,583
SKELETOR: Teary
reconciliations can wait.

1596
01:26:38,125 --> 01:26:40,416
Now give me the Sword.

1597
01:26:42,750 --> 01:26:43,875
Release him.

1598
01:26:44,000 --> 01:26:47,291
Mm-hmm... I said it first.

1599
01:26:47,458 --> 01:26:48,458
Release him!

1600
01:26:49,208 --> 01:26:52,583
You don't want to play that
game with me, you naughty boy.

1601
01:26:52,750 --> 01:26:54,666
I play to win and...

1602
01:26:56,041 --> 01:26:57,541
(IN DEEPER VOICE) I cheat.

1603
01:26:58,833 --> 01:27:01,083
-(EVIL HORDE GROWLING)
-(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1604
01:27:01,208 --> 01:27:02,666
(SNARLS)

1605
01:27:04,791 --> 01:27:06,750
(EVIL HORDE SNARLING
AND GROWLING)

1606
01:27:07,625 --> 01:27:10,333
-(GROWLING)
-(GOAT MAN CHUCKLING)

1607
01:27:13,125 --> 01:27:14,125
Take it.

1608
01:27:16,000 --> 01:27:17,166
You can try.

1609
01:27:17,750 --> 01:27:19,375
(GUARDS GROWLING)

1610
01:27:20,958 --> 01:27:23,291
(ALL GRUNTING)

1611
01:27:32,166 --> 01:27:33,625
(GOAT MAN GROWLS)

1612
01:27:33,750 --> 01:27:35,375
(SCREAMS)

1613
01:27:36,125 --> 01:27:37,666
(SCREAMS)

1614
01:27:38,083 --> 01:27:39,750
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1615
01:27:41,875 --> 01:27:43,083
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1616
01:27:46,583 --> 01:27:47,708
(ADAM GROANS)

1617
01:27:47,833 --> 01:27:49,041
(KING RANDOR GASPS)

1618
01:27:51,000 --> 01:27:52,541
(EVIL HORDE GROWLING)

1619
01:27:52,916 --> 01:27:55,083
(ELECTRIFYING ROCK
MUSIC PLAYING)

1620
01:27:55,208 --> 01:27:56,750
(GASPS) No. No!

1621
01:27:56,875 --> 01:27:58,000
(GUARD YELPS)

1622
01:27:58,708 --> 01:28:00,541
(WHIMPERS, SCREAMS)

1623
01:28:03,041 --> 01:28:04,041
(GASPS)

1624
01:28:04,833 --> 01:28:06,125
(LAUGHS)

1625
01:28:06,791 --> 01:28:08,625
-(ADAM GRUNTS)
-(GROANS)

1626
01:28:13,750 --> 01:28:15,291
(ROARS)

1627
01:28:19,291 --> 01:28:20,500
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1628
01:28:25,583 --> 01:28:27,041
(BOTH GRUNT)

1629
01:28:27,166 --> 01:28:28,375
(STRAINING)

1630
01:28:32,000 --> 01:28:33,125
(SCREAMING)

1631
01:28:35,541 --> 01:28:37,666
-(ADAM GRUNTING)
-(CONTINUES SCREAMING)

1632
01:28:50,208 --> 01:28:51,583
(ADAM GROANS)

1633
01:28:51,708 --> 01:28:53,958
(GUARDS GROWLING AND GRUNTING)

1634
01:28:55,625 --> 01:28:56,833
(STRAINING)

1635
01:28:56,958 --> 01:28:58,208
(ADAM GROWLS)

1636
01:29:01,416 --> 01:29:03,875
(YELLS)

1637
01:29:08,916 --> 01:29:10,250
(ROARS)

1638
01:29:10,375 --> 01:29:13,041
-(DRAMATIC ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)
-(ALL GRUNTING)

1639
01:29:20,041 --> 01:29:21,625
(WEAPON POWERS UP)

1640
01:29:22,166 --> 01:29:23,583
(SCREAMING)

1641
01:29:23,708 --> 01:29:25,625
(ALL GRUNTING)

1642
01:29:38,875 --> 01:29:40,041
-(YELLS)
-(ADAM GRUNTS)

1643
01:29:41,083 --> 01:29:43,333
-(GRUNTS)
-(GROWLING)

1644
01:29:43,458 --> 01:29:44,666
(ADAM ROARS)

1645
01:29:45,833 --> 01:29:46,875
(GOAT MAN GROWLS)

1646
01:29:49,416 --> 01:29:50,666
(SNARLING)

1647
01:29:57,875 --> 01:29:59,083
(GOAT MAN GROANS)

1648
01:29:59,791 --> 01:30:00,875
(GOAT MAN GRUNTS)

1649
01:30:01,958 --> 01:30:04,166
-(ADAM GRUNTS)
-(GOAT MAN CHOKING)

1650
01:30:04,875 --> 01:30:06,666
(GROANS)

1651
01:30:06,791 --> 01:30:08,500
(SCREAMING)

1652
01:30:08,625 --> 01:30:09,958
(GROWLING IN PAIN)

1653
01:30:11,166 --> 01:30:12,708
(ADAM GRUNTS)

1654
01:30:12,833 --> 01:30:14,958
-(GOAT MAN CHOKING)
-(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1655
01:30:15,750 --> 01:30:18,000
-(GRUNTS)
-(GOAT MAN SCREAMING)

1656
01:30:19,208 --> 01:30:20,208
(BODY THUDS)

1657
01:30:20,333 --> 01:30:22,083
(PANTING)

1658
01:30:24,250 --> 01:30:25,916
(GROWLING)

1659
01:30:30,083 --> 01:30:31,291
(ADAM YELLS)

1660
01:30:32,458 --> 01:30:34,041
(CRACKLING)

1661
01:30:34,166 --> 01:30:35,291
(GRUNTS)

1662
01:30:35,416 --> 01:30:37,958
(RECITING INCANTATION
IN UNKNOWN LANGUAGE)

1663
01:30:38,083 --> 01:30:39,416
(ADAM GRUNTING)

1664
01:30:41,250 --> 01:30:43,416
(EVIL-LYN CONTINUES
RECITING INCANTATION)

1665
01:30:46,125 --> 01:30:48,625
(SKELETOR CLEARING THROAT)

1666
01:30:49,583 --> 01:30:52,458
Very good, Evil-Lyn,
he's... he's frozen.

1667
01:30:53,875 --> 01:30:56,541
Bravo, Prince Adam.
Quite the show.

1668
01:30:56,916 --> 01:30:58,583
But to what end?

1669
01:30:59,333 --> 01:31:02,000
Face me like a man.

1670
01:31:03,041 --> 01:31:04,958
(SIGHS) Well, A,
I don't have a face,

1671
01:31:05,083 --> 01:31:07,000
and, B, I don't want to.

1672
01:31:08,125 --> 01:31:11,500
Besides, it's my turn
to put on a show.

1673
01:31:12,291 --> 01:31:14,166
What do you think, Papa?

1674
01:31:14,583 --> 01:31:15,916
Shall I let him watch

1675
01:31:16,041 --> 01:31:18,333
as I slay you
with his own sword?

1676
01:31:18,458 --> 01:31:19,916
(LAUGHS)

1677
01:31:20,041 --> 01:31:21,041
SKELETOR: Oh, yes.

1678
01:31:21,625 --> 01:31:23,541
(GIGGLES TAUNTINGLY)

1679
01:31:24,250 --> 01:31:25,708
(LAUGHS WICKEDLY)

1680
01:31:27,166 --> 01:31:28,333
(YELLS)

1681
01:31:30,916 --> 01:31:32,250
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1682
01:31:32,375 --> 01:31:34,000
(CRUMBLING)

1683
01:31:39,958 --> 01:31:40,958
No.

1684
01:31:41,750 --> 01:31:43,750
-(SKELETOR GRUNTS)
-No!

1685
01:31:46,833 --> 01:31:47,875
(PANTS)

1686
01:31:51,458 --> 01:31:52,791
(GRUNTING)

1687
01:31:57,458 --> 01:31:58,875
-Dad?
-(GROANS WEAKLY)

1688
01:32:00,333 --> 01:32:01,333
KING RANDOR: Adam.

1689
01:32:03,041 --> 01:32:04,416
Let me see you.

1690
01:32:06,083 --> 01:32:07,666
(LAUGHS TEARFULLY)

1691
01:32:07,791 --> 01:32:09,083
There you are.

1692
01:32:10,250 --> 01:32:14,041
Oh, you took your time,
but you came back.

1693
01:32:14,833 --> 01:32:18,250
Yeah, I've changed so much.

1694
01:32:19,583 --> 01:32:24,208
I'm not that, uh... I'm not
that weak little boy anymore.

1695
01:32:24,333 --> 01:32:26,375
(CHUCKLES) Yeah.

1696
01:32:27,333 --> 01:32:29,250
Now I'm everything
you wanted me to be.

1697
01:32:30,166 --> 01:32:31,166
Well, what...

1698
01:32:32,541 --> 01:32:34,500
Well, what did I want
you to be?

1699
01:32:37,833 --> 01:32:39,166
Someone else.

1700
01:32:41,250 --> 01:32:43,000
(ADAM BREATHES HEAVILY)

1701
01:32:43,458 --> 01:32:47,875
-No. No. Hey. Hey, that's...
-(SOBBING)

1702
01:32:48,583 --> 01:32:50,833
That's not what I wanted.

1703
01:32:53,666 --> 01:32:58,208
As a boy,
you were so very small.

1704
01:32:59,666 --> 01:33:01,416
The world just...

1705
01:33:02,875 --> 01:33:05,208
just seemed so big for you.

1706
01:33:05,958 --> 01:33:08,375
So I tried to make you strong

1707
01:33:09,166 --> 01:33:12,333
because I wanted...
I wanted to protect you.

1708
01:33:13,791 --> 01:33:16,000
It was the only way
I knew how.

1709
01:33:17,375 --> 01:33:18,416
There are...

1710
01:33:20,000 --> 01:33:24,666
Oh, there were so many things
I should have said.

1711
01:33:25,166 --> 01:33:28,333
Dad, it's okay.
(LAUGHS TEARFULLY)

1712
01:33:28,458 --> 01:33:30,583
-Hmm?
-It's... It's okay. (SNIFFLES)

1713
01:33:30,708 --> 01:33:32,958
KING RANDOR: I wish
I understood better then.

1714
01:33:34,458 --> 01:33:36,458
I wish I had let you...

1715
01:33:39,458 --> 01:33:40,625
be you.

1716
01:33:41,791 --> 01:33:43,291
(BREATHES SHARPLY)

1717
01:33:44,791 --> 01:33:47,291
(KING RANDOR
BREATHES LABORIOUSLY)

1718
01:33:47,416 --> 01:33:50,375
Dad, no. Wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait! Wait!

1719
01:33:51,500 --> 01:33:54,833
Dad, you... you can't close
your eyes yet. (SNIFFLES)

1720
01:33:56,208 --> 01:33:57,625
(CHUCKLES) I didn't...

1721
01:33:57,750 --> 01:33:59,250
I didn't get
to say it yet. I...

1722
01:33:59,375 --> 01:34:01,333
(BREATH SHUDDERING)

1723
01:34:01,458 --> 01:34:07,125
I... I need you to hear...
hear me say it.

1724
01:34:07,916 --> 01:34:09,208
(CRYING)

1725
01:34:09,333 --> 01:34:11,666
(SOLEMN MUSIC PLAYING)

1726
01:34:18,958 --> 01:34:20,875
SKELETOR: And so
you both submit.

1727
01:34:30,166 --> 01:34:31,291
(ADAM GRUNTS)

1728
01:34:39,791 --> 01:34:40,958
(GROANS)

1729
01:34:42,458 --> 01:34:43,666
Are you okay, lad?

1730
01:34:44,375 --> 01:34:45,500
You changed back.

1731
01:34:45,791 --> 01:34:47,791
(SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING)

1732
01:34:57,541 --> 01:34:59,666
(CRYING SOFTLY)

1733
01:35:01,833 --> 01:35:03,750
-Mom.
-QUEEN MARLENA: Oh. (SIGHS)

1734
01:35:07,708 --> 01:35:08,708
Mm.

1735
01:35:11,125 --> 01:35:12,125
ADAM: He's gone.

1736
01:35:15,208 --> 01:35:16,916
(ADAM CRIES SOFTLY)

1737
01:35:17,541 --> 01:35:18,750
(QUEEN MARLENA WHIMPERS)

1738
01:35:19,958 --> 01:35:20,958
QUEEN MARLENA: Oh.

1739
01:35:22,500 --> 01:35:24,583
SKELETOR: <i>Oh,</i>
<i>so long I've waited.</i>

1740
01:35:27,333 --> 01:35:29,708
Now I shall be reborn

1741
01:35:30,750 --> 01:35:34,500
and the universe
shall quake in my shadow.

1742
01:35:36,666 --> 01:35:39,458
By the Power of Grayskull,

1743
01:35:39,916 --> 01:35:41,208
I...

1744
01:35:41,708 --> 01:35:42,958
have...

1745
01:35:43,458 --> 01:35:46,750
the Power! (LAUGHS GIDDILY)

1746
01:35:49,750 --> 01:35:52,750
(GRUNTING)

1747
01:35:53,416 --> 01:35:55,583
(SKELETOR STRAINING)

1748
01:35:56,291 --> 01:35:57,666
(GRUNTS, SIGHS)

1749
01:35:59,083 --> 01:36:01,416
Was that right?
Did I mess up the words?

1750
01:36:01,583 --> 01:36:03,416
No, those are the words.

1751
01:36:03,541 --> 01:36:05,666
Once more with feeling,
perhaps?

1752
01:36:06,000 --> 01:36:07,666
Don't test me, woman.

1753
01:36:09,125 --> 01:36:11,541
(GRUNTING LOUDLY)

1754
01:36:11,666 --> 01:36:13,333
Why isn't it working?

1755
01:36:14,416 --> 01:36:15,500
(GROWLING)

1756
01:36:16,041 --> 01:36:17,625
Wait! (GROANS)

1757
01:36:17,750 --> 01:36:20,166
Tell me why it isn't working.

1758
01:36:20,875 --> 01:36:23,333
There's a ritual
I can perform.

1759
01:36:23,458 --> 01:36:24,708
(GRUNTS)

1760
01:36:24,833 --> 01:36:27,041
If we return the Sword
to Grayskull,

1761
01:36:27,791 --> 01:36:30,958
to its altar,
I promise you it will work.

1762
01:36:31,083 --> 01:36:35,333
-(CHOKING)
-It had better.

1763
01:36:35,916 --> 01:36:37,416
-(GRUNTS)
-(EVIL-LYN GASPING)

1764
01:36:37,541 --> 01:36:39,208
Prepare my ship.

1765
01:36:40,416 --> 01:36:41,541
(WINCES)

1766
