let's crash their party!

2018
01:50:34,708 --> 01:50:36,541
DUNCAN: I got my invitation
right here.

2019
01:50:36,666 --> 01:50:38,083
ROBOTO: Well, no,
if you have an invitation,

2020
01:50:38,208 --> 01:50:39,541
-you're not really...
-(LAUGHS) Oh!

2021
01:50:42,916 --> 01:50:45,375
RSVP. I'm about
to shoot these assholes.

2022
01:50:47,416 --> 01:50:49,916
ROBOTO: You're really making
a mess of this party metaphor.

2023
01:50:50,625 --> 01:50:53,375
(LAUGHS) Don't this
feel great? Right?

2024
01:50:54,333 --> 01:50:55,416
Oof!

2025
01:50:55,750 --> 01:50:57,500
They are not going
to get to that castle.

2026
01:50:57,666 --> 01:50:58,875
Not as long as I'm standing.

2027
01:50:59,041 --> 01:51:00,625
ROBOTO: You've barely been
upright since I met you.

2028
01:51:00,750 --> 01:51:03,166
-(SCOFFS)
-(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

2029
01:51:04,833 --> 01:51:06,458
DUNCAN: Hey, you got
any missiles left?

2030
01:51:06,833 --> 01:51:07,916
ROBOTO: Yes. One.

2031
01:51:08,041 --> 01:51:09,250
That's all we need.

2032
01:51:09,375 --> 01:51:10,958
(GUARDS YELLING)

2033
01:51:14,250 --> 01:51:15,250
(DUNCAN GRUNTS)

2034
01:51:15,833 --> 01:51:17,416
(GUARDS EXCLAIM)

2035
01:51:18,833 --> 01:51:19,958
(CREAKING)

2036
01:51:20,083 --> 01:51:22,291
(ALL SCREAMING)

2037
01:51:25,125 --> 01:51:27,291
(BOTH LAUGHING)

2038
01:51:28,583 --> 01:51:30,541
ROBOTO: Yes! Whoo-hoo!

2039
01:51:32,125 --> 01:51:33,208
DUNCAN: What is that?

2040
01:51:38,666 --> 01:51:40,083
Run! Run!

2041
01:51:41,791 --> 01:51:42,791
ROBOTO: Look out!

2042
01:51:42,916 --> 01:51:44,416
(DUNCAN GRUNTS)

2043
01:51:44,541 --> 01:51:45,625
(ROBOTO GRUNTS)

2044
01:51:47,541 --> 01:51:48,583
(DISTORTED) Duncan?

2045
01:51:50,333 --> 01:51:51,333
(ROBOTO SCREAMS)

2046
01:51:52,916 --> 01:51:54,875
(GASPING)

2047
01:51:55,875 --> 01:51:57,000
(GRUNTS)

2048
01:51:58,500 --> 01:51:59,541
(GRUNTS)

2049
01:52:00,166 --> 01:52:02,166
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

2050
01:52:04,666 --> 01:52:06,125
(GROWLS)

2051
01:52:06,250 --> 01:52:07,875
(DUNCAN YELLS)

2052
01:52:08,833 --> 01:52:10,208
(DUNCAN YELLS)

2053
01:52:12,541 --> 01:52:14,541
(DUNCAN GRUNTING)

2054
01:52:16,916 --> 01:52:18,750
-(GROWLS)
-DUNCAN: Remember me?

2055
01:52:19,791 --> 01:52:21,458
You remember who I used to be?

2056
01:52:21,583 --> 01:52:23,041
(BOTH GRUNTING)

2057
01:52:33,041 --> 01:52:34,625
Commander of the Royal Guard.

2058
01:52:35,250 --> 01:52:37,791
-King's Man-At-Arms.
-(GROANING)

2059
01:52:37,916 --> 01:52:40,500
-But today...
-(GROANS)

2060
01:52:40,625 --> 01:52:41,750
-(DUNCAN GRUNTS)
-(DEVICE BEEPS)

2061
01:52:41,875 --> 01:52:43,083
(BOTH GRUNTING)

2062
01:52:43,208 --> 01:52:45,875
-(DEVICE BEEPING RAPIDLY)
-(TRAP JAW SCREAMS)

2063
01:52:46,000 --> 01:52:47,500
...I'm a new man!

2064
01:52:50,916 --> 01:52:52,125
(GRUNTS)

2065
01:52:55,125 --> 01:52:57,125
(PANTING)

2066
01:53:00,916 --> 01:53:02,000
(GRUNTS)

2067
01:53:04,250 --> 01:53:06,625
(GROANING)

2068
01:53:07,250 --> 01:53:09,000
-Hey.
-ROBOTO: (DISTORTED) Duncan?

2069
01:53:09,166 --> 01:53:10,166
Roboto!

2070
01:53:11,833 --> 01:53:13,750
Don't you go
powering down on me.

2071
01:53:13,916 --> 01:53:15,333
ROBOTO:
It-It-It doesn't matter.

2072
01:53:15,500 --> 01:53:17,958
Existence is a series
of absurdities

2073
01:53:18,083 --> 01:53:20,500
leading to
infinite nothingness.

2074
01:53:20,625 --> 01:53:22,750
(EXHALES) That's my girl.

2075
01:53:24,041 --> 01:53:26,708
(SIGHS) That's my girl.

2076
01:53:27,541 --> 01:53:28,625
(SIGHS)

2077
01:53:33,958 --> 01:53:36,833
Stand still,
you muscle-bound oaf!

2078
01:53:37,000 --> 01:53:39,000
I'm trying to annihilate you!

2079
01:53:46,291 --> 01:53:48,375
(GRUNTS, BREATHING HEAVILY)

2080
01:53:48,500 --> 01:53:49,791
(STRAINS)

2081
01:53:55,041 --> 01:53:56,208
(GASPS)

2082
01:53:59,833 --> 01:54:01,041
(ADAM GRUNTS)

2083
01:54:04,083 --> 01:54:06,083
(GASPS, CHOKING)

2084
01:54:07,833 --> 01:54:09,833
(OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING)

2085
01:54:11,666 --> 01:54:13,208
(CONTINUES CHOKING)

2086
01:54:17,166 --> 01:54:19,125
Well, would you look at that?

2087
01:54:20,708 --> 01:54:23,000
It seems
your sword is worthless.

2088
01:54:23,750 --> 01:54:26,916
Nothing more than a cheap toy
to play with.

2089
01:54:27,208 --> 01:54:29,250
ADAM: That's not possible.

2090
01:54:29,708 --> 01:54:31,000
SKELETOR: I'm curious.

2091
01:54:32,166 --> 01:54:35,333
Without this, what are you?

2092
01:54:36,500 --> 01:54:38,375
Who are you?

2093
01:54:39,083 --> 01:54:42,791
-Let's have a look. (SNARLS)
-(GRUNTS)

2094
01:54:43,583 --> 01:54:45,458
-(SNARLS)
-(FLESH SEARING)

2095
01:54:45,583 --> 01:54:46,708
(STRAINS)

2096
01:54:48,416 --> 01:54:49,750
(YELLS)

2097
01:54:49,875 --> 01:54:51,000
(GASPS)

2098
01:54:51,833 --> 01:54:53,416
-(GROANS)
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

2099
01:54:54,833 --> 01:54:56,041
MAN: <i>Unleash the beast, dude!</i>

2100
01:54:56,166 --> 01:54:57,375
WOMAN: <i>That's gold,</i>
<i>bro, right there.</i>

2101
01:54:57,500 --> 01:54:58,958
MAN 2: <i>Sick flex, bro.</i>

2102
01:54:59,833 --> 01:55:01,458
Could I level with you, Adam?

2103
01:55:01,625 --> 01:55:03,125
I was never really buying

2104
01:55:03,250 --> 01:55:05,500
that whole
beefcake barbarian thing.

2105
01:55:06,250 --> 01:55:09,208
I don't think
you ever were the tough guy.

2106
01:55:09,708 --> 01:55:12,583
I suspect you were the runt.

2107
01:55:13,083 --> 01:55:14,791
And those
that didn't bully you,

2108
01:55:14,958 --> 01:55:17,666
well, they felt sorry for you.

2109
01:55:17,791 --> 01:55:19,291
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

2110
01:55:19,583 --> 01:55:20,958
Catch! (GRUNTS)

2111
01:55:22,958 --> 01:55:25,458
It wasn't like that.

2112
01:55:25,833 --> 01:55:26,833
No?

2113
01:55:27,416 --> 01:55:28,583
(SKELETOR GRUNTS)

2114
01:55:28,708 --> 01:55:29,791
(GASPS)

2115
01:55:29,916 --> 01:55:31,625
(BREATH SHUDDERING)

2116
01:55:35,708 --> 01:55:37,000
JULIE: What was it like?

2117
01:55:38,708 --> 01:55:39,708
What?

2118
01:55:39,875 --> 01:55:41,250
Your home planet.

2119
01:55:42,291 --> 01:55:43,583
What was it like?

2120
01:55:44,458 --> 01:55:47,208
Well, it was, um... (SWALLOWS)

2121
01:55:48,041 --> 01:55:50,250
(CHUCKLES) It was beautiful.

2122
01:55:51,875 --> 01:55:53,083
(SIGHS)

2123
01:55:54,500 --> 01:55:56,500
Like nothing
you've ever seen before.

2124
01:55:56,791 --> 01:55:59,208
Oh, my God,
have you ever been to Sedona?

2125
01:55:59,791 --> 01:56:00,791
What? (GASPS)

2126
01:56:01,458 --> 01:56:03,458
(SNARLS) Ah, now this place,

2127
01:56:03,583 --> 01:56:05,208
-this is more your thing.
-(GROANING)

2128
01:56:05,333 --> 01:56:06,875
A world of grays and beiges

2129
01:56:07,000 --> 01:56:09,500
and a constant
humiliating failure.

2130
01:56:09,625 --> 01:56:10,625
(ADAM YELLS)

2131
01:56:10,750 --> 01:56:12,708
(GRUNTS, GROANS SOFTLY)

2132
01:56:13,291 --> 01:56:15,041
(PANTING)

2133
01:56:16,416 --> 01:56:18,250
Adam! Can this wait?

2134
01:56:18,375 --> 01:56:19,791
I have a performance review
with Darryl.

2135
01:56:19,916 --> 01:56:21,333
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

2136
01:56:21,458 --> 01:56:23,625
-(PEOPLE SCREAMING)
-(ADAM GROANS)

2137
01:56:23,750 --> 01:56:25,500
(MAN GROANS)

2138
01:56:25,625 --> 01:56:26,625
Who's the demon, Adam?

2139
01:56:27,333 --> 01:56:29,875
ADAM: He's the bad guy.
He broke my sword!

2140
01:56:30,583 --> 01:56:32,416
Here we go again
with the Sword!

2141
01:56:32,833 --> 01:56:34,416
While I conquered
an entire planet,

2142
01:56:34,541 --> 01:56:36,750
you were here, uh... uh...

2143
01:56:39,250 --> 01:56:40,875
What even is this?

2144
01:56:41,041 --> 01:56:42,583
It's Human Resources.

2145
01:56:42,750 --> 01:56:44,375
Human resources?

2146
01:56:45,208 --> 01:56:47,791
Oh, Adam, you naughty boy.

2147
01:56:48,041 --> 01:56:49,041
Oh, come on.

2148
01:56:49,208 --> 01:56:51,125
SKELETOR: Oh, you can pretend
to be the hero

2149
01:56:51,250 --> 01:56:52,875
with your giant muscles,

2150
01:56:53,041 --> 01:56:55,291
that big long sword dangling

2151
01:56:55,416 --> 01:56:58,625
-between your glorious thighs.
-(CHOKING)

2152
01:56:58,750 --> 01:57:00,666
But you'll always be
a failure.

2153
01:57:01,500 --> 01:57:05,125
-Eternia isn't your home.
-(CONTINUES CHOKING)

2154
01:57:05,625 --> 01:57:09,125
It's a dream
of something you're not.

2155
01:57:10,291 --> 01:57:12,250
(CLICKING TEETH)

2156
01:57:15,875 --> 01:57:17,125
And that dream...

2157
01:57:19,000 --> 01:57:20,250
is over.

2158
01:57:20,750 --> 01:57:22,708
-(CHOKES)
-(TEELA GASPS)

2159
01:57:22,833 --> 01:57:24,125
(GASPING)

2160
01:57:30,416 --> 01:57:32,333
(GRUNTING)

2161
01:57:32,458 --> 01:57:33,583
(GROANS)

2162
01:57:35,166 --> 01:57:36,541
(GASPING)

2163
01:57:36,791 --> 01:57:37,791
Adam!

2164
01:57:38,458 --> 01:57:39,458
Adam!

2165
01:57:39,916 --> 01:57:41,750
-(PANTING)
-HUSSEIN: Adam!

2166
01:57:43,708 --> 01:57:46,125
Hey, Adam,

2167
01:57:46,708 --> 01:57:47,666
are you okay?

2168
01:57:47,833 --> 01:57:48,875
Yeah.

2169
01:57:50,083 --> 01:57:53,083
I... I just think
I might have died.

2170
01:57:55,625 --> 01:57:56,625
Damn.

2171
01:57:56,750 --> 01:57:58,375
Uh, that's heavy, brother.

2172
01:57:59,333 --> 01:58:01,083
Well, you let me know
if you need anything.

2173
01:58:01,666 --> 01:58:04,875
Uh, I think you might have
dropped one.

2174
01:58:05,041 --> 01:58:06,041
So...

2175
01:58:07,375 --> 01:58:08,375
there you go.

2176
01:58:08,541 --> 01:58:10,083
All right. (PANTING)

2177
01:58:11,166 --> 01:58:14,166
Kind of convenient to die
right before the rent is due.

2178
01:58:14,666 --> 01:58:16,208
No, I... I'll...
I'll handle it.

2179
01:58:18,166 --> 01:58:19,916
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

2180
01:58:20,916 --> 01:58:22,125
(WIND BLOWS)

2181
01:58:22,791 --> 01:58:25,000
(ETHEREAL MUSIC PLAYING)

2182
01:58:25,125 --> 01:58:26,875
(PAPERS RUSTLING)

2183
01:58:35,541 --> 01:58:36,541
SORCERESS: Get up.

2184
01:58:38,125 --> 01:58:40,458
It... It's a talking bird.

2185
01:58:40,791 --> 01:58:41,791
Yes.

2186
01:58:42,208 --> 01:58:43,291
That's weird.

2187
01:58:43,458 --> 01:58:44,833
Uh, you had a talking cat.

2188
01:58:45,083 --> 01:58:47,125
(SIGHS) That's a fair point.

2189
01:58:48,541 --> 01:58:50,166
So this is it, huh?

2190
01:58:53,333 --> 01:58:54,500
I'm dead?

2191
01:58:54,791 --> 01:58:55,791
Perhaps.

2192
01:58:56,291 --> 01:58:59,208
-Get up!
-(GRUNTS)

2193
01:59:00,000 --> 01:59:01,916
(PANTING)

2194
01:59:03,166 --> 01:59:04,750
How can I get up
if I'm dead, huh?

2195
01:59:05,291 --> 01:59:06,583
You have the Power.

2196
01:59:07,333 --> 01:59:08,333
No.

2197
01:59:10,833 --> 01:59:12,041
Not anymore.

2198
01:59:14,750 --> 01:59:16,250
The Sword's broken.

2199
01:59:16,500 --> 01:59:17,583
What sword?

2200
01:59:19,250 --> 01:59:22,708
The Sword... of Power.

2201
01:59:23,166 --> 01:59:25,916
Oh, that. What about it?

2202
01:59:26,916 --> 01:59:28,791
(LAUGHING) It's... Well...

2203
01:59:29,708 --> 01:59:32,375
It's... It's
the Sword of Power.

2204
01:59:35,541 --> 01:59:38,500
"Whosoever wields the Sword

2205
01:59:39,166 --> 01:59:40,666
"shall hold the Power."

2206
01:59:40,833 --> 01:59:43,125
Adam, when you hold aloft
your magic sword,

2207
01:59:43,250 --> 01:59:44,791
what words do you say?

2208
01:59:46,125 --> 01:59:47,958
By the Power of Grayskull...

2209
01:59:48,125 --> 01:59:50,333
SORCERESS: Yes, go on.

2210
01:59:51,541 --> 01:59:52,625
(SIGHS)

2211
01:59:54,583 --> 01:59:56,291
I have the Power.

2212
01:59:56,458 --> 01:59:59,250
That's right.
You have the Power.

2213
01:59:59,791 --> 02:00:00,791
Not the Sword.

2214
02:00:01,708 --> 02:00:02,708
(ECHOING) You.

2215
02:00:03,625 --> 02:00:05,791
-I chose you.
-(BREATHING HEAVILY)

2216
02:00:09,541 --> 02:00:11,958
In the hands
of past champions,

2217
02:00:12,083 --> 02:00:14,500
the Power has been
brute strength.

2218
02:00:16,083 --> 02:00:20,250
But in yours,
it becomes so much more.

2219
02:00:21,208 --> 02:00:25,208
It is understanding,
it is empathy.

2220
02:00:25,375 --> 02:00:27,125
It is humanity.

2221
02:00:29,583 --> 02:00:32,416
That is why I chose you
as the vessel, Adam.

2222
02:00:33,833 --> 02:00:35,166
I am the vessel.

2223
02:00:37,166 --> 02:00:38,458
Now you're ready.

2224
02:00:39,083 --> 02:00:41,166
(BREATHING DEEPLY)

2225
02:00:43,416 --> 02:00:45,166
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

2226
02:00:46,208 --> 02:00:47,375
(GASPING)

2227
02:00:47,500 --> 02:00:48,708
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

2228
02:00:50,250 --> 02:00:52,250
(BREATHING RAGGEDLY)

2229
02:00:55,375 --> 02:00:57,625
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

2230
02:00:59,375 --> 02:01:01,250
(SOFT CHIMING)

2231
02:01:03,375 --> 02:01:05,416
(ROUSING MUSIC PLAYING)

2232
02:01:15,875 --> 02:01:17,000
(SNAPS)

2233
02:01:22,458 --> 02:01:24,500
(ECHOING) By the Power
of Grayskull,

2234
02:01:24,666 --> 02:01:28,083
-I have the Power!
-(CRACKLING)

2235
02:01:29,166 --> 02:01:30,500
Oh, balls.

2236
02:01:39,250 --> 02:01:41,875
-(PANTING)
-(HOPEFUL MUSIC PLAYING)

2237
02:01:42,000 --> 02:01:43,666
(MEKANECK GRUNTS, GASPS)

2238
02:01:46,333 --> 02:01:47,583
-Yeah!
-(ETERNIA WARRIORS CHEERING)

2239
02:01:47,708 --> 02:01:48,833
(CHUCKLING)

2240
02:01:49,916 --> 02:01:51,041
(FISTO GRUNTS)

2241
02:01:53,583 --> 02:01:54,916
(GASPS)

2242
02:02:06,541 --> 02:02:07,791
(SIGHS)

2243
02:02:08,666 --> 02:02:10,541
(MUSIC CRESCENDOES)

2244
02:02:12,500 --> 02:02:13,791
-(SIGHS)
-(MUSIC STOPS)

2245
02:02:14,750 --> 02:02:15,750
Skeletor...

2246
02:02:18,833 --> 02:02:20,583
I have a proposition for you.

2247
02:02:22,583 --> 02:02:23,750
Why don't we...

2248
02:02:25,083 --> 02:02:29,083
end this cycle of violence
and talk?

2249
02:02:31,250 --> 02:02:32,333
Just talk.

2250
02:02:32,916 --> 02:02:34,125
(CRINGER GRUNTS IN CONFUSION)

2251
02:02:34,250 --> 02:02:36,250
You destroyed my world.

2252
02:02:36,583 --> 02:02:39,625
You have caused
so much pain and suffering.

2253
02:02:39,791 --> 02:02:42,541
And maybe that's because
you couldn't be king.

2254
02:02:44,166 --> 02:02:46,750
Maybe it's because you weren't
loved enough as a child.

2255
02:02:48,750 --> 02:02:50,916
Doesn't matter to me
who you are.

2256
02:02:52,083 --> 02:02:54,333
What matters is what you do.

2257
02:02:56,083 --> 02:02:59,750
So do something right.

2258
02:03:07,000 --> 02:03:08,000
SKELETOR: Hmm.

2259
02:03:10,083 --> 02:03:12,333
(LAUGHING)

2260
02:03:21,250 --> 02:03:23,208
Oh, you... you boob.

2261
02:03:23,375 --> 02:03:25,958
You muscle-bound milquetoast.

2262
02:03:26,125 --> 02:03:29,041
There is no right
that will be done here.

2263
02:03:29,208 --> 02:03:32,791
There is no good in me
that you might uncover.

2264
02:03:33,458 --> 02:03:36,750
There is nothing you can say
that will change my nature,

2265
02:03:36,916 --> 02:03:40,250
for I... I am...

2266
02:03:42,750 --> 02:03:44,083
a villain.

2267
02:03:45,625 --> 02:03:47,416
(INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING)

2268
02:03:47,541 --> 02:03:50,916
And... (GRUNTS)
does it feel good. (CHUCKLES)

2269
02:03:52,375 --> 02:03:53,583
(GRUNTS)

2270
02:03:54,208 --> 02:03:56,125
-(GRUNTS)
-(SKELETOR SCREECHES)

2271
02:04:04,583 --> 02:04:06,375
-(SKELETOR GRUNTS)
-(GROANS)

2272
